IEAVAR00 CSECT ,                                                   0001 00003000
@MAINENT DS    0H                                                  0001 00004000
         USING *,@15                                               0001 00005000

         DC    AL2(@EP00001-@MAINENT)                                   00007000
         DC    AL1(16)                                             0001 00008000
         DC    C'IEAVAR00  74.306'                                 0001 00009000
IEAVAER0 DS    0H                                                  0001 00010000

         B     @PROLOG                                             0001 00012000

@PROLOG  BALR  @06,0                                               0001 00016000

*INITCODE:                                                         0135 00277000

*/*                                                                  */ 01590000
*/*    ATTENTION SCHEDULER DIAGNOSTIC SUBROUTINE                     */ 01591000
*/*                                                                  */ 01592000
*/********************************************************************/ 01593000
*/*                                                                  */ 01594000
*/*    THIS ROUTINE RECEIVES CONTROL FROM THE ESTAE MAINLINE ROUTINE */ 01595000
*/*    IT IS THE RESPONSIBILITY OF THIS ROUTINE TO DETERMINE WHETHER */ 01596000
*/*    TO RETRY OR CONTINUE WITH TERMINATION. THE REGISTERS AT ENTRY */ 01597000
*/*    TO THIS ROUTINE ARE    R2    ADDRESS OF RCTD                  */ 01598000
*/*                           R3    ADDRESS OF SDWA                  */ 01599000
*/*                           R6    BASE REGISTER                    */ 01600000
*/*                           R13   RTM SAVE AREA ADDR               */ 01601000
*/*                           R14   RETURN ADDRESS                   */ 01602000
*/*                           R15   ENTRY ADDRESS                    */ 01603000
*/*                                                                  */ 01604000
*/********************************************************************/ 01605000
*                                                                  0474 01606000
*ATTNDIAG:                                                         0474 01607000
*   PROC OPTIONS(NOSAVE,NOSAVEAREA);                               0474 01608000
ATTNDIAG DS    0H                                                  0475 01609000
*   RETPTR4=RETPTR14;               /* SAVE RETURN ADDRESS           */ 01610000
         LR    RETPTR4,RETPTR14                                    0475 01611000
*   IF SDWANRBE='1'B|RCTDDUMP='1'B THEN/* IF RCTS RB WAS NOT IN    0476 01612000
*                                      CONTROL OR A DUMP HAS BEEN  0476 01613000
*                                      REQUESTED -DUMP LSQA          */ 01614000
         TM    SDWANRBE(SDWAPTR),B'01000000'                       0476 01615000
         BO    @RT00476                                            0476 01616000
         TM    RCTDDUMP(RCTDPTR2),B'00000010'                      0476 01617000
         BNO   @RF00476                                            0476 01618000
@RT00476 DS    0H                                                  0477 01619000
*     DO;                                                          0477 01620000
*       CALL DUMPRTN;               /* INVOKE THE DUMP ROUTINE TO  0478 01621000
*                                      DUMP LSQA                     */ 01622000
         BAL   @14,DUMPRTN                                         0478 01623000
*       RCR15=0;                    /* INDICATE CONTINUE WITH      0479 01624000
*                                      TERMINATION                   */ 01625000
         SLR   RCR15,RCR15                                         0479 01626000

./  ADD  SSI=43030619,NAME=IEAVAR01
         TITLE 'IEAVAR01 - RCT COMMON PROCESSING                       *00001000
                        '                                               00002000
IEAVAR01 CSECT ,                                                   0001 00003000
@MAINENT DS    0H                                                  0001 00004000
         USING *,@15                                               0001 00005000
         B     @PROLOG                                             0001 00006000
         DC    AL1(16)                                             0001 00007000
         DC    C'IEAVAR01  74.306'                                 0001 00008000
         DROP  @15                                                      00009000
@PROLOG  STM   @14,@12,12(@13)                                     0001 00010000
         BALR  @12,0                                               0001 00011000
@PSTART  DS    0H                                                  0001 00012000
         USING @PSTART,@12                                         0001 00013000
*                                      THE RCTD - THIS REDUCES THE 0039 00014000
*                                      AMOUNT OF CODE PRODUCED       */ 00015000
*   RCTDRCTR=CPMODFLG;              /* SET COMMON PROCESSING       0040 00016000
*                                      FOOTPRINT AND CLEAR OTHER   0040 00017000
*                                      MODULE/FUNCTION FOOTPRINTS    */ 00018000
         MVC   RCTDRCTR(4,RCTDR13),@CB00915                        0040 00019000
*   RETADDR9=RETPTR14;              /* SAVE THE RETURN ADDRESS IN A     00020000
*                                      REG BECAUSE THE COPY IN THE 0041 00021000
*                                      REGISTER SAVE AREA WILL BE  0041 00022000
*                                      OVERLAYED                     */ 00023000
         LR    RETADDR9,RETPTR14                                   0041 00024000
*   RCTDTPTR=ADDR(RCTDTECB);        /* INITIALIZE THE FIRST ECB    0042 00025000
*                                      ADDRESS OF THE ECB LIST TO  0042 00026000
*                                      POINT TO THE TERMINATION ECB  */ 00027000
         LA    @15,RCTDTECB(,RCTDR13)                              0042 00028000
         ST    @15,RCTDTPTR(,RCTDR13)                              0042 00029000
*   RCTDWPTR=ADDR(ASCBECB);         /* INITIALIZE THE SECOND/LAST ECB   00030000
*                                      ADDRESS TO POINT TO THE WORK     00031000
*                                      ECB                           */ 00032000
         LA    @15,ASCBECB(,ASCBPTR)                               0043 00033000
         ST    @15,RCTDWPTR(,RCTDR13)                              0043 00034000
*   RCTDECBE='1'B;                  /* TURN ON THE HIGH ORDER BIT OF    00035000
*                                      THE LAST ECB ADDRESS IN THE 0044 00036000
*                                      ECB LIST                      */ 00037000
         OI    RCTDECBE(RCTDR13),B'10000000'                       0044 00038000
*   RFY                                                            0045 00039000
*     RETPTR14 UNRSTD;              /* UNRESTRICT REG 14 SINCE ITS 0045 00040000
*                                      CONTENTS HAVE BEEN SAVED      */ 00041000
*   GENERATE CODE REFS(RCTDISAV,BASER12) SETS(RCTDISAV) NODEFS NOFLOWS; 00042000
        STM RETPTR14,BASER12,12(RCTDR13)    SAVE CURRENT REGISTERS -    00043000
*                                           BASE AND RETURN REGISTER    00044000
*                                           IN PARTICULAR               00045000
*                                                                  0047 00046000
*/********************************************************************/ 00047000
*/*                                                                  */ 00048000
*/*    LOOP - WAITING FOR TERMINATION REQUEST                        */ 00049000
*/*                                                                  */ 00050000
*/*    QUIESCE IS INVOKED WHICH WILL WAIT FOR A FUNCTIONAL           */ 00051000
*/*    REQUEST. FOR ANYTHING OTHER THAN A SWAP-OUT REQUEST,          */ 00052000
*/*    CONTROL IS RETURNED SO THAT COMMON PROCESSING CAN             */ 00053000
*/*    CHECK THE REQUEST AND ROUTE CONTROL TO THE APPROPRIATE        */ 00054000
*/*    ROUTINE(S). FOR A SWAP-OUT REQUEST (ASCBFQU), QUIESCE WILL    */ 00055000
*/*    HANDLE THIS PROCESS PRIOR TO RETURNING CONTROL TO COMMON      */ 00056000
*/*    PROCESSING. THIS WILL HELP TO MINIMIZE THE POSSIBILITY OF     */ 00057000
*/*    PAGE FAULTS IN THE SWAP-OUT PATH.                             */ 00058000
*/*                                                                  */ 00059000
*/********************************************************************/ 00060000
*                                                                  0047 00061000
*WAITPREP:                          /* LABEL USED TO IDENTIFY TOP OF    00062000
*                                      WAIT LOOP                     */ 00063000
*   DO UNTIL(RCTDPOST='1'B);        /* PERFORM THE FOLLOWING UNTIL 0047 00064000
*                                      THE TERMINATION ECB IS POSTED    00065000
*                                                            @Z30JQVB*/ 00066000
WAITPREP DS    0H                                                  0047 00067000
@DL00047 DS    0H                                                  0048 00068000
*     RCTDRTRY=0;                   /* CLEAR THE RECOVERY RECURSION     00069000
*                                      INDICATOR             @Z30JQVB*/ 00070000
         SLR   @08,@08                                             0048 00071000
         ST    @08,RCTDRTRY(,RCTDR13)                              0048 00072000
*IEAVAR1A:                          /* RETRY ENTRY POINT FOR WAIT  0049 00073000
*                                      LOOP                  @Z30JQVB*/ 00074000
*     RCTDRCTR=BR2QFLG;             /* INDICATE QUIESCE IS ABOUT TO     00075000
*                                      BE ENTERED AND CLEAR OTHER  0049 00076000
*                                      FUNCTION INDICATORS THAT MAY     00077000
*                                      HAVE BEEN SET IN THIS LOOP  0049 00078000
*                                                            @Z30JQVB*/ 00079000
IEAVAR1A MVC   RCTDRCTR(4,RCTDR13),@CB00917                        0049 00080000
*     CALL IEAVAR02;                /* BRANCH TO THE RCT QUIESCE   0050 00081000
*                                      MODULE                @Z30JQVB*/ 00082000
         L     @15,CVTQUIS(,CVTPTR)                                0050 00083000
         BALR  @14,@15                                             0050 00084000
*     RCTDRCTR=LOOKFLG;             /* RESET FOOTPRINTS TO INDICATE     00085000
*                                      LOOKING FOR WORK      @Z30JQVB*/ 00086000
         MVC   RCTDRCTR(4,RCTDR13),@CB00919                        0051 00087000
*     CALL WORKCK;                  /* INVOKE SUBROUTINE TO CHECK FOR   00088000
*                                      OTHER FUNCTION FLAGS  @Z30JQVB*/ 00089000
         LA    @15,WORKCK                                          0052 00090000
         BALR  @14,@15                                             0052 00091000
*LOOPBACK:                                                         0053 00092000
*   END;                            /*                       @Z30JQVB*/ 00093000
LOOPBACK DS    0H                                                  0053 00094000
@DE00047 TM    RCTDPOST(RCTDR13),B'01000000'                       0053 00095000
         BNO   @DL00047                                            0053 00096000
*                                                                  0054 00097000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00098000
*   /*                                                               */ 00099000
*   /* MODULE EXIT CODE                                              */ 00100000
*   /*                                                               */ 00101000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00102000
*                                                                  0054 00103000
*TERMPOST:                          /* LABEL USED FOR TESTING ONLY   */ 00104000
*   RCTDBR2T='1'B;                  /* SET FUNCTION FLAG THAT      0054 00105000
*                                      INDICATES THE RETURN TO RCT 0054 00106000
*                                      INIT/TERM IS BEING PERFORMED  */ 00107000
TERMPOST OI    RCTDBR2T(RCTDR13),B'00100000'                       0054 00108000
*   RCTDISAV(4)=RETADDR9;           /* STORE RETURN ADDRESS, TO RCT     00109000
*                                      INIT/TERM, IN REGISTER 14   0055 00110000
*                                      LOCATION OF SAVE AREA SO THAT    00111000
*                                      IT WILL CONTAIN THE CORRECT 0055 00112000
*                                      VALUE WHEN THE RETURN IS    0055 00113000
*                                      ATTEMPTED                     */ 00114000
         ST    RETADDR9,RCTDISAV+12(,RCTDR13)                      0055 00115000
*ENDR01:                                                           0056 00116000
*   RETURN;                         /* RETURN TO RCT INIT/TERM     0056 00117000
*                                                            @Z30JQVB*/ 00118000
@EL00001 DS    0H                                                  0056 00119000
@EF00001 DS    0H                                                  0056 00120000
@ER00001 LM    @14,@12,12(@13)                                     0056 00121000
         BR    @14                                                 0056 00122000
*                                                                  0057 00123000
*/********************************************************************/ 00124000
*/*                                                                  */ 00125000
*/*      LOOKING FOR A FUNCTIONAL REQUEST                            */ 00126000
*/*                                                                  */ 00127000
*/*      THIS SUBROUTINE CHECKS THE OTHER FUNCTIONAL REQUEST         */ 00128000
*/*      INDICATORS (ASCBFRS, RCTDPOST AND TSBATTNC) TO DETERMINE    */ 00129000
*/*      WHETHER   RESTORE, TERMINATION  OR  THE ATTENTION           */ 00130000
*/*      SCHEDULER SHOULD BE INVOKED, INITIALIZES THE INTERFACE      */ 00131000
*/*      REGISTERS, AND INVOKES THE APPROPRIATE MODULE(S).           */ 00132000
*/*                                                                  */ 00133000
*/********************************************************************/ 00134000
*                                                                  0057 00135000
*WORKCK:                            /* NO ENTRY LINKAGE IS REQUESTED */ 00136000
*   PROC OPTIONS(NOSAVE,NOSAVEAREA,ENTREG,RETREG,NOPARMREG);       0057 00137000
         B     @EL00001                                            0057 00138000
WORKCK   DS    0H                                                  0058 00139000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0058 00140000
*    (RETPTR8,                      /* RESTRICT REG 8 THROUGHOUT THIS   00141000
*                                      SUBROUTINE - IT WILL CONTAIN     00142000
*                                      THE RETURN ADDRESS            */ 00143000
*     RETPTR14) RSTD;               /* REG 14 IS RESTRICTED UNTIL ITS   00144000
*                                      CONTENTS CAN BE SAVED         */ 00145000
*   RETPTR8=RETPTR14;               /* SAVE RETURN ADDRESS IN A    0059 00146000
*                                      REGISTER                      */ 00147000
         LR    RETPTR8,RETPTR14                                    0059 00148000
*   RFY                                                            0060 00149000
*     RETPTR14 UNRSTD;              /* REGISTER 14 NO LONGER NEED BE    00150000
*                                      RESTRICTED                    */ 00151000
*   IF ASCBFRS='1'B                 /* DETERMINE WHETHER THE ADDRESS    00152000
*                                      SPACE IS TO BE RESTORED       */ 00153000
*     THEN                                                         0061 00154000
         TM    ASCBFRS(ASCBPTR),B'01000000'                        0061 00155000
         BNO   @RF00061                                            0061 00156000
*     DO;                           /* WHEN RESTORE IS REQUESTED   0062 00157000
*                                      PERFORM THE FOLLOWING         */ 00158000
*       RCTDBR2R='1'B;              /* SET FUNCTION FLAG INDICATING     00159000
*                                      RESTORE IS BEING INVOKED      */ 00160000
         OI    RCTDBR2R(RCTDR13),B'00001000'                       0063 00161000
*       CALL IEAVAR03;              /* BRANCH TO THE RCT RESTORE   0064 00162000
*                                      MODULE                        */ 00163000
         L     @15,@CV00935                                        0064 00164000
         BALR  @14,@15                                             0064 00165000
*       RCTDRCTR=LOOKFLG;           /* RESET FOOTPRINTS TO INDICATE -   00166000
*                                      IN COMMON PROCESSING - LOOKING   00167000
*                                      FOR WORK                      */ 00168000
         MVC   RCTDRCTR(4,RCTDR13),@CB00919                        0065 00169000
*     END;                                                         0066 00170000
*   ELSE                                                           0067 00171000
*     ;                             /* CONTINUE PROCESSING WHEN    0067 00172000
*                                      RESTORE NOT REQUESTED         */ 00173000
@RF00061 DS    0H                                                  0068 00174000
*   IF RCTDPOST='0'B THEN           /* CHECK WHETHER THE TERMINATION    00175000
*                                      ECB HAS NOT BEEN POSTED     0068 00176000
*                                                            @Z30JQVB*/ 00177000
         TM    RCTDPOST(RCTDR13),B'01000000'                       0068 00178000
         BNZ   @RF00068                                            0068 00179000
*     DO;                           /* CONTINUE PROCESSING WHEN    0069 00180000
*                                      TERMINATION NOT REQUESTED   0069 00181000
*                                                            @Z30JQVB*/ 00182000
*       IF ASCBTSBÂ¬=0               /* DETERMINE WHETHER A TSB EXISTS*/ 00183000
*         THEN                                                     0070 00184000
         L     @15,ASCBTSB(,ASCBPTR)                               0070 00185000
         LTR   @15,@15                                             0070 00186000
         BZ    @RF00070                                            0070 00187000
*         DO;                       /* TSB EXISTS - FOREGROUND     0071 00188000
*                                      ADDRESS SPACE - PERFORM THE 0071 00189000
*                                      FOLLOWING                     */ 00190000
*TERM:                                                             0072 00191000
*           ;                       /* LABEL USED FOR TESTING ONLY   */ 00192000
TERM     DS    0H                                                  0073 00193000
*           RFY                                                    0073 00194000
*             TSBPTR RSTD;          /* RESTRICT REG CONTAINING THE 0073 00195000
*                                      TSB POINTER                   */ 00196000
*           TSBPTR=ASCBTSB;         /* INITIALIZE THE TSB POINTER    */ 00197000
*                                                                  0074 00198000
         L     TSBPTR,ASCBTSB(,ASCBPTR)                            0074 00199000
*           /*********************************************************/ 00200000
*           /*                                                       */ 00201000
*           /* ESTABLISH ADDRESSABILITY TO THE TSB                   */ 00202000
*           /*                                                       */ 00203000
*           /*********************************************************/ 00204000
*                                                                  0075 00205000
*           GENERATE CODE(USING TSB,TSBPTR )                       0075 00206000
*           NODEFS NOSETS NOREFS NOFLOWS;                          0075 00207000
         USING TSB,TSBPTR                                               00208000
*           IF TSBATTNCÂ¬=0          /* DETERMINE WHETHER THERE IS AN    00209000
*                                      ATTENTION EXIT REQUEST        */ 00210000
*             THEN                                                 0076 00211000
         CLI   TSBATTNC,0                                          0076 00212000
         BE    @RF00076                                            0076 00213000
*             DO;                   /* WHEN THERE IS A REQUEST FOR AN   00214000
*                                      ATTENTION EXIT PERFORM THE  0077 00215000
*                                      FOLLOWING                     */ 00216000
*               GENERATE CODE(DROP  TSBPTR )                       0078 00217000
*               NODEFS NOSETS NOREFS NOFLOWS;                      0078 00218000
         DROP  TSBPTR                                                   00219000
*               RFY                                                0079 00220000
*                 TSBPTR UNRSTD;    /* UNRESTRICT BASE REG FOR TSB -    00221000
*                                      DO NOT REFER TO TSB AFTER THIS   00222000
*                                      POINT UNLESS THIS REG IS    0079 00223000
*                                      RE-INITIALIZED                */ 00224000
*               RCTDBR2A='1'B;      /* SET FUNCTION FLAG INDICATING     00225000
*                                      THE ATTENTION SCHEDULER IS  0080 00226000
*                                      BEING INVOKED                 */ 00227000
         OI    RCTDBR2A(RCTDR13),B'00000100'                       0080 00228000
*               CALL IEAVAR04;      /* BRANCH TO THE ATTENTION     0081 00229000
*                                      SCHEDULER MODULE              */ 00230000
         L     @15,@CV00936                                        0081 00231000
         BALR  @14,@15                                             0081 00232000
*               RCTDRCTR=LOOKFLG;   /* RESET FOOTPRINTS TO INDICATE -   00233000
*                                      IN COMMON PROCESSING - LOOKING   00234000
*                                      FOR WORK                      */ 00235000
         MVC   RCTDRCTR(4,RCTDR13),@CB00919                        0082 00236000
*             END;                                                 0083 00237000
*           ELSE                                                   0084 00238000
*             ;                     /* CONTINUE PROCESSING WHEN    0084 00239000
*                                      ATTENTION REQUEST NOT       0084 00240000
*                                      INDICATED                     */ 00241000
@RF00076 DS    0H                                                  0085 00242000
*         END;                                                     0085 00243000
*       ELSE                                                       0086 00244000
*         ;                         /* CONTINUE PROCESSING WHEN TSB     00245000
*                                      DOES NOT EXIST                */ 00246000
@RF00070 DS    0H                                                  0087 00247000
*     END;                          /*                       @Z30JQVB*/ 00248000
*   ELSE                                                           0088 00249000
*     ;                             /* WHEN THE TERMINATION ECB IS 0088 00250000
*                                      POSTED RETURN SO THAT       0088 00251000
*                                      TERMINATION PROCESSING CAN BE    00252000
*                                      INVOKED               @Z30JQVB*/ 00253000
@RF00068 DS    0H                                                  0089 00254000
*   RFY                                                            0089 00255000
*     RETPTR14 RSTD;                /* RESTRICT REG 14 DURING RETURN    00256000
*                                      LINKAGE                       */ 00257000
*   RETPTR14=RETPTR8;               /* RESTORE REG 14 WITH RETURN  0090 00258000
*                                      ADDRESS                       */ 00259000
         LR    RETPTR14,RETPTR8                                    0090 00260000
*   END WORKCK;                     /* RETURN TO TOP SEGMENT         */ 00261000
@EL00002 DS    0H                                                  0091 00262000
@EF00002 DS    0H                                                  0091 00263000
@ER00002 BR    @14                                                 0091 00264000
*   END IEAVAR01                                                   0092 00265000
*                                                                  0092 00266000

*                                                                  0143 00171000
*/********************************************************************/ 00172000
*/*                                                                  */ 00173000
*/*    THIS SECTION OF CODE WILL DO THE FOLLOWING PROCESSING FOR     */ 00174000
*/*    A QUICK CHECK TO DETERMINE IF THE ADDRESS SPACE IS IN         */ 00175000
*/*    LONG WAIT:                                                    */ 00176000
*/*      - SET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO INDICATE THE SETLOCK        */ 00177000
*/*        MACRO IS BEING INVOKED TO OBTAIN THE LOCAL LOCK FOR       */ 00178000
*/*        THE FIRST TIME.                                           */ 00179000
*/*      - INVOKE THE LOCKOBT SUBROUTINE TO OBTAIN THE               */ 00180000
*/*        LOCAL LOCK AND ESTABLISH ITS RECOVERY EXIT.               */ 00181000
*/*      - INITIALIZE REGISTER 1 TO ZERO. THIS WILL BE THE           */ 00182000
*/*        INDICATOR TO THE SYSTEM RESOURCES MANAGER (SRM)           */ 00183000
*/*        IF THE ADDRESS SPACE IS NOT IN LONG WAIT.                 */ 00184000
*/*      - SET UP THE MASK TO CHECK FOR READY TASKS WHEN TCBS        */ 00185000
*/*        ARE SET NON-DISPATCHABLE FOR SWAPPING OUT.                */ 00186000
*/*      - INVOKE THE TCBCHECK SUBROUTINE WHICH WILL SCAN THE        */ 00187000
*/*        TCB PRIORITY QUEUE LOOKING AT THE WAIT COUNT IN THE       */ 00188000
*/*        RBS  AND THE NON-DISPATCHABILITY FLAGS IN EACH TCB IN     */ 00189000
*/*        SEARCH FOR A READY TASK. IF THE READY STATUS WAS NOT      */ 00190000
*/*        FOUND,THEN THIS SUBROUTINE WILL SET THE HIGH ORDER        */ 00191000
*/*        BIT OF REGISTER 1  TO INDICATE THE ADDRESS SPACE IS       */ 00192000
*/*        IN LONG WAIT.                                             */ 00193000
*/*      - SET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO INDICATE THE SETLOCK        */ 00194000
*/*        MACRO IS BEING INVOKED TO RELEASE THE LOCAL LOCK          */ 00195000
*/*        FOR THE FIRST TIME.                                       */ 00196000
*/*      - INVOKE THE LOCKREL SUBROUTINE TO RELEASE THE              */ 00197000
*/*        LOCAL LOCK AND DELETE ITS RECOVERY EXIT.                  */ 00198000
*/*                                                                  */ 00199000
*/********************************************************************/ 00200000
*                                                                  0143 00201000

*/********************************************************************/ 00221000
*/*                                                                  */ 00222000
*/*    THIS SECTION OF CODE WILL DO THE FOLLOWING PROCESSING FOR     */ 00223000
*/*    QUIESCE'S FIRST COMMUNICATION WITH THE SYSTEM RESOURCES       */ 00224000
*/*    MANAGER (SRM) TO INDICATE QUIESCE PROCESSING HAS STARTED:     */ 00225000
*/*      - SET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO INDICATE SYSEVENT 12        */ 00226000
*/*        IS BEING INVOKED.                                         */ 00227000
*/*      - ISSUE THE SYSEVENT 12 MACRO TO INFORM SRM THAT            */ 00228000
*/*        QUIESCE HAS STARTED, OR QUIESCE HAS STARTED AND           */ 00229000
*/*        THE ADDRESS SPACE IS CONSIDERED TO BE IN LONG WAIT        */ 00230000
*/*        IF THE HIGH ORDER BIT OF REGISTER 1 IS ON (1).            */ 00231000
*/*      - CHECK THE RETURN CODE IN THE LOW ORDER BYTE OF            */ 00232000
*/*        REGISTER 1:                                               */ 00233000
*/*         - X'00' INDICATES THAT QUIESCE SHOULD CONTINUE           */ 00234000
*/*           TO PREPARE THE ADDRESS SPACE TO BE SWAPPED.            */ 00235000
*/*         - X'08' INDICATES THAT QUIESCE SHOULD RESTORE            */ 00236000
*/*           THE ADDRESS SPACE TO ITS ORIGINAL STATUS AND           */ 00237000
*/*           TERMINATE PROCESSING.                                  */ 00238000
*/*                                                                  */ 00239000
*/********************************************************************/ 00240000
*                                                                  0152 00241000

*/*      FOLLOWING PROCESSING WHEN THE SYSTEM RESOURCES              */ 00257000

*                                                                  0166 00301000
*/********************************************************************/ 00302000
*/*                                                                  */ 00303000
*/*      THE SYSTEM RESOURCES MANAGER (SRM) HAS INDICATED            */ 00304000
*/*      THAT QUIESCE SHOULD CONTINUE PROCESSING AND PREPARE         */ 00305000
*/*      THE ADDRESS SPACE TO BE SWAPPED.                            */ 00306000
*/*                                                                  */ 00307000
*/********************************************************************/ 00308000
*/*                                                                  */ 00309000
*/*      THIS SECTION OF CODE WILL DO THE FOLLOWING PROCESSING       */ 00310000
*/*      TO PURGE I/O:                                               */ 00311000
*/*        - CLEAR THE AREA FOR THE PURGE PARAMETER LIST TO ZEROS.   */ 00312000
*/*        - SET UP THE PURGE PARAMETER LIST TO INDICATE THE         */ 00313000
*/*          FOLLOWING:                                              */ 00314000
*/*            -  DO NOT PURGE THE RB CHAIN FOR ASYNCRONOUSLY        */ 00315000
*/*               SCHEDULED ROUTINES.                                */ 00316000
*/*            -  OPTION BYTE 2 IS PRESENT AND CONTAINS VALID        */ 00317000
*/*               INFORMATION.                                       */ 00318000
*/*            -  THE ADDRESS OF THE ANCHOR FROM WHICH THE           */ 00319000
*/*               PURGED I/O REQUEST LIST WILL BE CHAINED.           */ 00320000
*/*            -  MEMORY PURGE SPECIFIED.                            */ 00321000
*/*            -  PURGE I/O REQUESTS SO THAT WHEN THEY ARE           */ 00322000
*/*               RESTORED THEY WILL BE ASSOCIATED WITH THE          */ 00323000
*/*               TCB THAT ORIGINATED THEM.                          */ 00324000
*/*            -  THE ASID OF THE MEMORY TO WHICH I/O                */ 00325000
*/*               REQUESTS ARE ASSOCIATED.                           */ 00326000
*/*        - SET UP REGISTER 1 TO POINT TO THE PURGE                 */ 00327000
*/*          PARAMETER LIST.                                         */ 00328000
*/*        - SET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO INDICATE SVC 16           */ 00329000
*/*          IS BEING INVOKED.                                       */ 00330000
*/*        - ISSUE SVC 16 TO PURGE I/O FOR ALL TASKS IN              */ 00331000
*/*          THE ADDRESS SPACE.                                      */ 00332000

*/*          LONGER OWNS THE PURGE RESOURCE, SYSZEC16.               */ 00334000

*/*          TO RELEASE CONTROL OF THE PURGE RESOURCE.               */ 00336000

*/*                                                                  */ 00511000
*/*      THIS SECTION OF CODE WILL DO THE FOLLOWING PROCESSING       */ 00512000
*/*      TO OBTAIN THE LOCKS THAT ARE NEEDED TO DETERMINE IF         */ 00513000
*/*      THE ADDRESS SPACE IS IN LONG WAIT:                          */ 00514000

*/*          MACRO IS BEING INVOKED TO OBTAIN THE LOCAL LOCK         */ 00516000
*/*          FOR THE SECOND TIME.                                    */ 00517000
*/*        - INVOKE THE LOCKOBT SUBROUTINE TO  OBTAIN                */ 00518000
*/*          THE LOCAL LOCK AND ESTABLISH ITS RECOVERY               */ 00519000
*/*          EXIT.                                                   */ 00520000
*/*        - SET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO INDICATE QUIESCE          */ 00521000
*/*          HAS THE GLOBAL DISPATCHER LOCK.                         */ 00522000
*/*        - SET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO INDICATE THE SETLOCK      */ 00523000
*/*          MACRO IS BEING INVOKED TO OBTAIN THE GLOBAL             */ 00524000
*/*          DISPATCHER LOCK FOR THE FIRST TIME.                     */ 00525000
*/*        - ISSUE THE SETLOCK MACRO TO OBTAIN THE GLOBAL            */ 00526000
*/*          DISPATCHER LOCK. IT IS NECESSARY THAT QUIESCE           */ 00527000
*/*          HOLDS THE GLOBAL DISPATCHER LOCK WHEN SEARCHING         */ 00528000
*/*          THE SPL FOR A ''QUIESCEABLE'' SRB.                      */ 00529000
*/*        - INVOKE THE SETCHECK SUBROUTINE TO CHECK THE RETURN      */ 00530000
*/*          CODE FROM SETLOCK.                                      */ 00531000
*/*                                                                  */ 00532000

*                                                                  0211 00534000

*                                                                  0217 00550000
*/********************************************************************/ 00551000
*/*                                                                  */ 00552000
*/*      THIS SECTION OF CODE WILL DO THE FOLLOWING PROCESSING       */ 00553000
*/*      TO DETERMINE IF THE ADDRESS SPACE IS IN LONG WAIT:          */ 00554000
*/*        - INITIALIZE REGISTER 1 TO ZERO. THIS WILL BE             */ 00555000
*/*          THE INDICATOR TO THE SYSTEM RESOURCES MANAGER           */ 00556000
*/*          (SRM) IF THE ADDRESS SPACE IS NOT IN LONG WAIT.         */ 00557000
*/*        - CHECK THE LOCAL SPL FOR ANY ''QUIESCEABLE'' SRBS.       */ 00558000
*/*          IF ANY EXIST, THEN THE ADDRESS SPACE IS NOT IN          */ 00559000
*/*          LONG WAIT AND FURTHER TESTING IS UNNECESSARY.           */ 00560000
*/*        - IN EITHER CASE, INVOKE THE GLOBDISP SUBROUTINE          */ 00561000
*/*          TO RELEASE THE GLOBAL DISPATCHER LOCK.                  */ 00562000
*/*        - TO CONTINUE LONG WAIT TESTING, CHECK FOR ANY            */ 00563000
*/*          OUTSTANDING I/O. IF THE ADDRESS IN THE ANCHOR FOR       */ 00564000
*/*          THE PURGED I/O REQUEST LIST IS X'FFFFFF',THEN  NO       */ 00565000
*/*          I/O REQUESTS WERE PURGED SO CONTINUE TESTING.           */ 00566000
*/*          OTHERWISE, THE ADDRESS SPACE IS NOT IN LONG             */ 00567000
*/*          WAIT AND FURTHER TESTING IS UNNECESSARY.                */ 00568000
*/*        - TO CONTINUE LONG WAIT TESTING, CHECK FOR ANY            */ 00569000
*/*          ASYNCHRONOUS EXITS (IQES AND/OR RQES). IF ANY           */ 00570000
*/*          ARE QUEUED AND HAVE NOT BEEN PROCESSED FOR              */ 00571000
*/*          THIS ADDRESS SPACE, THEN THE ADDRESS SPACE              */ 00572000
*/*          IS NOT IN LONG WAIT AND FURTHER TESTING IS              */ 00573000
*/*          UNNECESSARY.                                            */ 00574000
*/*        - TO CONTINUE LONG WAIT TESTING, DETERMINE IF             */ 00575000
*/*          A TSB EXISTS. IF ONE EXISTS, ESTABLISH                  */ 00576000
*/*          ADDRESSABILITY TO IT AND CHECK FOR ANY                  */ 00577000
*/*          ATTENTION REQUESTS. IF ANY EXIST, THEN THE              */ 00578000
*/*          ADDRESS SPACE IS NOT IN LONG WAIT AND                   */ 00579000
*/*          FURTHER TESTING IS UNNECESSARY. ADDRESSABILITY          */ 00580000
*/*          TO THE TSB IS DELETED.                                  */ 00581000
*/*        - TO CONTINUE LONG WAIT TESTING WHEN A TSB                */ 00582000
*/*          DOES NOT EXIST OR THERE ARE NO ATTENTION                */ 00583000
*/*          REQUESTS, THE FOLLOWING IS DONE:                        */ 00584000
*/*            - SET UP THE MASK TO CHECK FOR READY                  */ 00585000
*/*              TASKS WHEN TCBS ARE SET NON-DISPATCHABLE            */ 00586000
*/*              FOR SWAPPING OUT AND SRBS ARE STOPPED.              */ 00587000
*/*            - INVOKE THE TCBCHECK SUBROUTINE WHICH                */ 00588000
*/*              WILL SCAN THE TCB PRIORITY QUEUE LOOKING            */ 00589000
*/*              AT THE WAIT COUNT IN THE RBS AND                    */ 00590000
*/*              NON-DISPATCHABILITY FLAGS IN EACH TCB               */ 00591000
*/*              IN SEARCH FOR A READY TASK. LONG WAIT               */ 00592000
*/*              TESTING IS COMPLETED HERE. IF THE READY             */ 00593000
*/*              STATUS WAS NOT FOUND THEN THIS SUBROUTINE           */ 00594000
*/*              WILL SET THE HIGH ORDER BIT OF REGISTER 1           */ 00595000
*/*              TO INDICATE THE ADDRESS SPACE IS IN LONG            */ 00596000
*/*              WAIT.                                               */ 00597000
*/*                                                                  */ 00598000

*/*                                                                  */ 00673000
*/*      THIS SECTION OF CODE WILL DO THE FOLLOWING PROCESSING       */ 00674000

*                                                                  0250 00702000
*/********************************************************************/ 00703000
*/*                                                                  */ 00704000
*/*      THIS SECTION OF CODE WILL DO THE FOLLOWING PROCESSING       */ 00705000
*/*      TO CHECK THE RETURN CODE IN REGISTER 1 FROM THE             */ 00706000
*/*      SYSTEM RESOURCES MANAGER (SRM) AND ACT ACCORDINGLY:         */ 00707000
*/*        - CHECK THE HIGH ORDER BYTE OF REGISTER 1 TO              */ 00708000
*/*          DETERMINE IF THE ADDRESS SPACE IS IN LONG WAIT.         */ 00709000
*/*           - X'80' INDICATES THE ADDRESS SPACE IS IN LONG         */ 00710000
*/*             WAIT. THEREFORE, SET THE TIMER SUPERVISION           */ 00711000
*/*             SUPPORT FLAG TO INDICATE THIS CONDITION.             */ 00712000
*/*             WAIT LIMIT SUPPORT WILL NOT BE PERFORMED. @OZ05805   */ 00713000
*/*           - X'00' INDICATES THE ADDRESS SPACE IS NOT IN          */ 00714000
*/*             LONG WAIT. THEREFORE, RESET THE TIMER SUPERVISION    */ 00715000
*/*             SUPPORT FLAG TO INDICATE THIS CONDITION.             */ 00716000
*/*          IT IS NECESSARY TO USE THE COMPARE AND SWAP             */ 00717000
*/*          INSTRUCTION IN SETTING THE TIMER SUPERVISION SUPPORT    */ 00718000
*/*          FLAGS TO INSURE SERIALIZATION OF THESE FIELDS.          */ 00719000
*/*               - TEST TO SEE IF WAIT LIMIT SUPPORT WILL BE DONE:  */ 00720000
*/*                    @OZ05805                                      */ 00721000
*/*                   - IF THE CPU CLOCK IS NOT BAD, THEN WAIT LIMIT */ 00722000
*/*                     SUPPORT IS PERFORMED SO THAT THE USER WILL   */ 00723000
*/*                     NOT BE CHARGED WITH THE TIME THAT HE WAS     */ 00724000
*/*                     SWAPPED OUT. THE STORE CLOCK INSTRUCTION IS  */ 00725000
*/*                     ISSUED TO GET THE CURRENT TIME STORED. THIS  */ 00726000
*/*                     WILL BE USED IN RESTORE PROCESSING TO        */ 00727000
*/*                     DETERMINE HOW LONG THE USER WAS SWAPPED OUT. */ 00728000
*/*                               @OZ05805                           */ 00729000
*/*                   - IF THE CPU CLOCK IS BAD, WAIT LIMIT SUPPORT  */ 00730000
*/*                     IS NOT PERFORMED.     @OZ05805               */ 00731000
*/*        - CHECK THE LOW ORDER BYTE OF REGISTER 1 TO               */ 00732000
*/*          DETERMINE IF THE SYSTEM RESOURCES MANAGER               */ 00733000
*/*          (SRM) WANTS THE ADDRESS SPACE SWAPPED.                  */ 00734000
*/*            - X'08' INDICATES THE ADDRESS SPACE SHOULD            */ 00735000
*/*              BE RESTORED, THEREFORE THE BACKOUT SUBROUTINE       */ 00736000
*/*              IS INVOKED TO HANDLE THIS CONDITION.                */ 00737000
*/*            - X'00' INDICATES THE ADDRESS SPACE SHOULD            */ 00738000
*/*              BE SWAPPED OUT, THEREFORE CONTINUE PROCESSING.      */ 00739000
*/*                                                                  */ 00740000
*/********************************************************************/ 00741000
*                                                                  0250 00742000
*               RFY                                                0250 00743000
*                (R6,                                              0250 00744000
*                 R8) RSTD;                                        0250 00745000
*               R6=CSFIELD;                                        0251 00746000

*                                                                  0272 00804000
*/********************************************************************/ 00805000
*/*                                                                  */ 00806000
*/*           THE SYSTEM RESOURCES MANAGER (SRM) INDICATED           */ 00807000
*/*           THAT QUIESCE SHOULD CONTINUE PROCESSING AND            */ 00808000
*/*           SWAP OUT THE ADDRESS SPACE.                            */ 00809000
*/*                                                                  */ 00810000
*/********************************************************************/ 00811000
*/*                                                                  */ 00812000
*/*           THIS SECTION OF CODE WILL DO THE FOLLOWING             */ 00813000
*/*           PROCESSING TO SWAP OUT THE ADDRESS SPACE:              */ 00814000
*/*             - ISSUE THE SETFRR MACRO TO DELETE THE               */ 00815000
*/*               RECOVERY EXIT FOR THE LOCKED CODE AND,             */ 00816000
*/*               HENCE, REMOVE QUIESCE'S FRR ADDRESS FROM           */ 00817000
*/*               THE LIFO STACK. THIS IS DONE TO GUARANTEE          */ 00818000
*/*               THAT WE KNOW THE STATUS OF THE FRR STACK           */ 00819000
*/*               UPON RETURNING FROM SWAP-OUT.                      */ 00820000
*/*             - SET UP THE FOLLOWING REGISTERS FOR THE             */ 00821000
*/*               INTERFACE TO SWAP-OUT:                             */ 00822000
*/*                - REGISTER 1 WITH THE ADDRESS OF THE ADDRESS      */ 00823000
*/*                  SPACE TO BE SWAPPED.                            */ 00824000
*/*                - REGISTER 13 WITH THE ADDRESS OF THE             */ 00825000
*/*                  SAVEAREA FOR SWAP-OUT TO USE.                   */ 00826000
*/*             - SET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO INDICATE THE         */ 00827000
*/*               SWAP-OUT ROUTINE IS BEING INVOKED.                 */ 00828000
*/*             - ISSUE A CALL TO THE SWAP-OUT ROUTINE USING         */ 00829000
*/*               ITS BRANCH ENTRY TO SWAP OUT THE ADDRESS           */ 00830000
*/*               SPACE.                                             */ 00831000
*/*             - FOR UNSUCCESSFUL COMPLETION (NON-ZERO RETURN       */ 00832000
*/*               CODE) OF THE SWAP-OUT REQUEST:                     */ 00833000
*/*                - RESET THE INDICATOR THAT THE ADDRESS            */ 00834000
*/*                  SPACE IS CONSIDERED SWAPPED OUT. THIS           */ 00835000
*/*                  WILL STOP USER READYS (SYSEVENT 4)              */ 00836000
*/*                  FROM BEING ISSUED TO SCHEDULE SRBS              */ 00837000
*/*                  FOR THIS ADDRESS SPACE. IT IS NECESSARY         */ 00838000
*/*                  TO USE COMPARE AND SWAP TO INSURE               */ 00839000
*/*                  SERIALIZATION OF THIS FIELD.                    */ 00840000
*/*                - RESET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO                 */ 00841000
*/*                  INDICATE SRBS ARE NO LONGER STOPPED.            */ 00842000
*/*                - SET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO INDICATE          */ 00843000
*/*                  SWAP-OUT FAILED.                                */ 00844000
*/*                - SAVE THE FAILING RETURN CODE.                   */ 00845000
*/*                - INVOKE THE ABENDEXT SUBROUTINE TO HANDLE        */ 00846000
*/*                  THE DETECTED ERROR.                             */ 00847000
*/*             - FOR SUCCESSFUL COMPLETION (ZERO RETURN CODE)       */ 00848000
*/*               OF THE SWAP-OUT REQUEST, CONTINUE PROCESSING.      */ 00849000
*/*                                                                  */ 00850000
*/********************************************************************/ 00851000

*/*                                                                  */ 00905000
*/*              THIS SECTION OF CODE WILL DO THE FOLLOWING          */ 00906000
*/*              PROCESSING TO WAIT UNTIL THE ADDRESS SPACE          */ 00907000
*/*              IS SWAPPED BACK INTO CORE:                          */ 00908000
*/*                - SET UP A REGISTER WITH QUIESCE'S FRR ADDRESS.   */ 00909000
*/*                - ISSUE THE SETFRR MACRO TO RE-ESTABLISH          */ 00910000

*/*                  THIS PLACES QUIESCE'S FRR ADDRESS ON THE        */ 00912000
*/*                  FRR LIFO STACK.                                 */ 00913000

*/*                    - STORE QUIESCE'S PSW IN ITS RB.              */ 00916000

*/*                - SET UP THE FOLLOWING REGISTERS FOR THE          */ 00918000

*/*                    - REGISTER 1 WITH THE ADDRESS OF THE          */ 00922000
*/*                      ECB BEING WAITED UPON.                      */ 00923000
*/*                - SET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO INDICATE          */ 00924000
*/*                  THE WAIT ROUTINE IS BEING INVOKED.              */ 00925000
*/*                - ISSUE A CALL TO THE WAIT ROUTINE USING          */ 00926000
*/*                  ITS BRANCH ENTRY. QUIESCE WILL BE POSTED        */ 00927000
*/*                  WHEN THE ADDRESS SPACE HAS BEEN SWAPPED         */ 00928000
*/*                  IN AND RESTORE PROCESSING IS TO BE DONE.        */ 00929000
*/*                  QUIESCE IS DEPENDENT UPON THE WAIT              */ 00930000
*/*                  ROUTINE TO RELEASE THE LOCAL LOCK AND           */ 00931000
*/*                  DELETE THE RECOVERY EXIT.                       */ 00932000
*/*                - RESET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO INDICATE        */ 00933000
*/*                  SRBS ARE NO LONGER STOPPED.                     */ 00934000
*/*                - CLEAR THE ECB FIELD.                            */ 00935000
*/*                                                                  */ 00936000

*/*                                                                  */ 01066000
*/*    THIS SECTION OF CODE IS THE BACKOUT SUBROUTINE WHICH          */ 01067000
*/*    WILL DO THE FOLLOWING PROCESSING TO RESTORE THE               */ 01068000
*/*    ADDRESS SPACE:                                                */ 01069000
*/*      - SAVE THE RETURN ADDRESS.                                  */ 01070000
*/*      - RESET THE FOLLOWING FLAGS TO INDICATE THE ADDRESS         */ 01071000
*/*        SPACE REMAINS IN CORE:                                    */ 01072000
*/*          - THE TIMER SUPERVISION SUPPORT FLAG THAT INDICATES     */ 01073000
*/*            THE MEMORY IS IN LONG WAIT.                           */ 01074000
*/*          - THE INDICATOR THAT THE ADDRESS SPACE IS               */ 01075000
*/*            CONSIDERED SWAPPED OUT. THIS WILL STOP USER           */ 01076000
*/*            READYS (SYSEVENT 4) FROM BEING ISSUED TO              */ 01077000
*/*            SCHEDULE SRBS FOR THIS ADDRESS SPACE.                 */ 01078000
*/*        IT IS NECESSARY TO USE COMPARE AND SWAP FOR BOTH          */ 01079000
*/*        OPERATIONS TO INSURE SERIALIZATION OF THESE FIELDS.       */ 01080000
*/*      - SET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO INDICATE THE SETLOCK        */ 01081000
*/*        MACRO IS BEING INVOKED TO RELEASE THE LOCAL LOCK          */ 01082000
*/*        FOR THE SECOND TIME.                                      */ 01083000
*/*      - INVOKE THE LOCKREL SUBROUTINE TO RELEASE THE              */ 01084000
*/*        LOCAL LOCK AND DELETE ITS RECOVERY EXIT.                  */ 01085000
*/*      - SET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO INDICATE THE STATUS         */ 01086000
*/*        MACRO IS BEING INVOKED TO RESTART SRBS.                   */ 01087000
*/*      - ISSUE THE STATUS MACRO TO RESTART THE DISPATCHING         */ 01088000
*/*        OF SRBS FOR THIS ADDRESS SPACE.                           */ 01089000
*/*      - RESET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO INDICATE SRBS ARE         */ 01090000
*/*        NO LONGER STOPPED.                                        */ 01091000
*/*      - ENTER DISPATCHER TO LET QUEUED SRBS RUN          @ZA10830 */ 01092000
*/*      - RESTORE THE RETURN ADDRESS.                               */ 01093000
*/*      - RETURN CONTROL TO QUIESCE'S MAINLINE.                     */ 01094000
*/*                                                                  */ 01095000
*/********************************************************************/ 01096000
*                                                                  0331 01097000

*                                                                  0349 01142000
*/********************************************************************/ 01143000
*/*                                                                  */ 01144000
*/*    THIS SECTION OF CODE IS THE SETCHECK SUBROUTINE WHICH         */ 01145000
*/*    WILL DO THE FOLLOWING PROCESSING TO CHECK THE RETURN          */ 01146000
*/*    CODE FROM SETLOCK:                                            */ 01147000
*/*      - FOR A ZERO (SUCCESSFUL) RETURN CODE FROM SETLOCK,         */ 01148000
*/*        RETURN CONTROL TO THE CALLER.                             */ 01149000
*/*      - FOR A NON-ZERO (FAILING) RETURN CODE FROM SETLOCK:        */ 01150000
*/*         - SET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO INDICATE SETLOCK         */ 01151000

*/*                                                                  */ 01225000
*/*    THIS SECTION OF CODE IS THE TCBCHECK SUBROUTINE WHICH         */ 01226000
*/*    WILL DO THE FOLLOWING PROCESSING TO DETERMINE IF THE          */ 01227000
*/*    ADDRESS SPACE IS IN LONG WAIT BY SCANNING THE TCB             */ 01228000
*/*    PRIORITY QUEUE FOR A READY TASK:                              */ 01229000
*/*      - ACCESS RCT'S FIRST SUBTASK.                               */ 01230000
*/*      - EXAMINE THE WAIT COUNT OF THE ASSOCIATED RB.              */ 01231000
*/*         - A ZERO WAIT COUNT MEANS THE RB IS READY TO RUN,        */ 01232000
*/*           SO EXAMINE THE TCB'S PRIMARY AND SECONDARY             */ 01233000
*/*           NON-DISPATCHABILITY FLAGS FOR A READY TCB.             */ 01234000
*/*            - IF A READY TCB IS FOUND, THEN IT IS                 */ 01235000
*/*              UNNECESSARY TO CONTINUE TESTING AND THE             */ 01236000
*/*              FOLLOWING IS DONE:                                  */ 01237000
*/*               - RESTORE THE POINTER TO RCT'S TCB.                */ 01238000
*/*               - RETURN CONTROL TO QUIESCE'S MAINLINE.            */ 01239000
*/*         - FOR A NON-ZERO RB WAIT COUNT OR A NOT READY TCB,       */ 01240000
*/*           THEN IT IS NECESSARY TO CONTINUE SCANNING THE          */ 01241000
*/*           TCB PRIORITY QUEUE, SO THE NEXT TCB IS ACCESSED.       */ 01242000
*/*           IF THE LAST TCB HAS BEEN EXAMINED WITHOUT A READY      */ 01243000
*/*           ONE BEING FOUND, THE FOLLOWING IS DONE:                */ 01244000
*/*            - SET UP REGISTER 1 TO INDICATE THE ADDRESS           */ 01245000
*/*              SPACE IS IN LONG WAIT.                              */ 01246000
*/*            - RESTORE THE POINTER TO RCT'S TCB.                   */ 01247000
*/*            - RETURN CONTROL TO QUIESCE'S MAINLINE.               */ 01248000
*/*                                                                  */ 01249000

*/*    THIS SECTION OF CODE IS THE ABENDEXT SUBROUTINE. WHEN         */ 01389000
*/*    QUIESCE RECEIVES AN UNEXPECTED RETURN CODE FROM A             */ 01390000
*/*    ROUTINE IT HAS INVOKED, THIS SUBROUTINE IS CALLED TO          */ 01391000

*/*            QUIESCE'S FRR ROUTINE                                 */ 01413000
*/*                                                                  */ 01414000
*/********************************************************************/ 01415000
*/*                                                                  */ 01416000
*/*    THIS SECTION OF CODE WILL GET CONTROL IN THE EVENT            */ 01417000
*/*    OF ANY ERROR ENCOUNTERED DURING LOCKED CODE PROCESSING        */ 01418000
*/*    FROM RTM VIA A LOAD PSW. REGISTERS AT INPUT ARE AS            */ 01419000
*/*    FOLLOWS:                                                      */ 01420000
*/*        REGISTER 0       ADDRESS OF A 200 BYTE WORK AREA          */ 01421000
*/*        REGISTER 1       ADDRESS OF THE SDWA                      */ 01422000
*/*        REGISTERS 2 - 13 INVALID                                  */ 01423000
*/*        REGISTER 14      RETURN ADDRESS                           */ 01424000
*/*        REGISTER 15      ENTRY POINT ADDRESS                      */ 01425000
*/*                                                                  */ 01426000
*/********************************************************************/ 01427000
*/*                                                                  */ 01428000
*/*    THE FOLLOWING INITIAL PROCESSING IS PERFORMED TO:             */ 01429000
*/*      - ESTABLISH ADDRESSABILITY FOR THIS ROUTINE.                */ 01430000
*/*      - LOAD THE BASE REGISTER WITH THE ENTRY POINT               */ 01431000
*/*        ADDRESS.                                                  */ 01432000
*/*      - ESTABLISH ADDRESSABILITY TO THE SDWA.                     */ 01433000
*/*      - CHECK THE SDWA INDICATOR TO DETERMINE IF THE              */ 01434000
*/*        ERROR WAS IN THIS ADDRESS SPACE:                          */ 01435000
*/*          - NON-ZERO INDICATES NOT THIS ADDRESS SPACE,            */ 01436000
*/*            SO ISSUE THE SETRP MACRO SPECIFYING THE               */ 01437000
*/*            FOLLOWING WHEN RETURNING TO RTM:                      */ 01438000
*/*              - ADDRESS OF THE SDWA.                              */ 01439000
*/*              - CONTINUE WITH TERMINATION.                        */ 01440000
*/*          - ZERO INDICATES THIS ADDRESS SPACE, SO                 */ 01441000
*/*            CONTINUE FRR PROCESSING.                              */ 01442000
*/*                                                                  */ 01443000
*/********************************************************************/ 01444000

*/*                                                                  */ 01540000
*/*      THIS SECTION OF CODE WILL DO THE FOLLOWING PROCESSING       */ 01541000
*/*      TO BEGIN DIAGNOSING THE ERROR:                              */ 01542000
*/*        - CHECK THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO DETERMINE IF            */ 01543000

*/*              TERMINATE THE CURRENT ADDRESS SPACE:                */ 01546000

*/*                    - MODULE, CSECT, AND FRR ID.                  */ 01555000

*/*                    - ADDRESS OF THE SDWA.                        */ 01557000
*/*                    - CONTINUE WITH TERMINATION.                  */ 01558000
*/*            - IF NO, THEN CONTINUE TO DIAGNOSE THE ERROR.         */ 01559000
*/*                                                                  */ 01560000
*/****************************************************************** */ 01561000
*                                                                  0428 01562000
*       IF RCTDSWOT='1'B THEN                                      0428 01563000
@RF00418 TM    RCTDSWOT(R2),B'00010000'                            0428 01564000

*         DO;                                                      0429 01566000
*           RFY                                                    0430 01567000

*                                                                  0446 01606000
*/********************************************************************/ 01607000
*/*                                                                  */ 01608000
*/*        THIS SECTION OF CODE WILL DO THE FOLLOWING                */ 01609000
*/*        PROCESSING WHEN THE ERROR OCCURRED PRIOR TO               */ 01610000
*/*        INVOKING SWAP-OUT:                                        */ 01611000
*/*          - CHECK THE CROSS COMMUNICATIONS RECOVERY FLAG          */ 01612000
*/*            TO DETERMINE IF THE GLOBAL DISPATCHER LOCK IS         */ 01613000
*/*            OWNED AT THIS TIME:                                   */ 01614000
*/*              - IF YES, THEN THE FOLLOWING IS DONE:               */ 01615000
*/*                  - RESET THE CROSS COMMUNICATIONS                */ 01616000
*/*                    RECOVERY FLAG TO INDICATE THE                 */ 01617000
*/*                    GLOBAL DISPATCHER LOCK IS NO LONGER           */ 01618000
*/*                    OWNED.                                        */ 01619000
*/*                  - ISSUE THE SETRP MACRO SPECIFYING THE          */ 01620000
*/*                    FOLLOWING WHEN RETURNING TO RTM:              */ 01621000
*/*                      - MODULE, CSECT, AND FRR ID.                */ 01622000
*/*                      - RECORD.                                   */ 01623000
*/*                      - FREE THE GLOBAL DISPATCHER AND            */ 01624000
*/*                        LOCAL LOCKS.                              */ 01625000
*/*                      - ADDRESS OF THE SDWA.                      */ 01626000
*/*                      - PERCOLATE.                                */ 01627000
*/*              - IF NO, THEN ISSUE THE SETRP MACRO                 */ 01628000
*/*                SPECIFYING THE FOLLOWING WHEN RETURNING           */ 01629000
*/*                TO RTM:                                           */ 01630000
*/*                  - MODULE, CSECT, AND FRR ID.                    */ 01631000
*/*                  - RECORD.                                       */ 01632000
*/*                  - FREE THE LOCAL LOCK.                          */ 01633000
*/*                  - ADDRESS OF THE SDWA.                          */ 01634000
*/*                  - PERCOLATE.                                    */ 01635000
*/*          - RELEASE THE REGISTER USED AS THE BASE FOR             */ 01636000
*/*            THIS FRR SINCE IT IS NO LONGER NEEDED.                */ 01637000
*/*                                                                  */ 01638000
*/********************************************************************/ 01639000
*                                                                  0446 01640000

./  ADD  SSI=62640404,NAME=IEAVAR03
         TITLE 'IEAVAR03, REGION CONTROL TASK RESTORE ROUTINE          *00001000
                        '                                               00002000
IEAVAR03 CSECT ,                                                   0001 00003000
@MAINENT DS    0H                                                  0001 00004000
         USING *,@15                                               0001 00005000
         B     @PROLOG                                             0001 00006000
         DC    AL1(16)                                             0001 00007000
         DC    C'IEAVAR03  76.264'                                 0001 00008000
         DROP  @15                                                      00009000
@PROLOG  STM   @14,@12,12(@13)                                     0001 00010000
   USING  IEAVAR03,R15              ESTABLISH ADDRESSABILITY            00011000
   L      R10,ENTRYPT               TO THE MODULE AT ITS                00012000
   DROP   R15                       ENTRY POINT                         00013000
   USING  IEAVAR03,R10                                                  00014000
RBPRFXLN EQU 64                                                         00015000
RBPRFLNA EQU 32                                                         00016000
PRBLEN   EQU 136                                                        00017000
SIRBLEN  EQU 200                                                        00018000
TIRBLEN  EQU 136                                                        00019000
IRBLEN   EQU 128                                                        00020000
SVRBLEN  EQU 200                                                        00021000
*                                                                  0096 00022000
*/********************************************************************/ 00023000
*/*                                                                  */ 00024000
*/*      EXECUTABLE CODE BEGINS HERE.                                */ 00025000
*/*        - ESTABLISH ADDRESSABILITY TO THE RCTD                    */ 00026000
*/*          FOR BETTER OPTIMIZATION.                                */ 00027000
*/*        - SET THE RESTORE PROCESSING RECOVERY                     */ 00028000
*/*          FOOTPRINT AND CLEAR THE OTHER                           */ 00029000
*/*          MODULE/FUNCTION FOOTPRINTS.                             */ 00030000
*/*                                                                  */ 00031000
*/********************************************************************/ 00032000
*                                                                  0096 00033000
*   R2=R13;                                                        0096 00034000
         LR    R2,R13                                              0096 00035000
*   RFY                                                            0097 00036000
*     RCTD BASED(R2);                                              0097 00037000
*   RCTDRCTR=INITMASK;                                             0098 00038000
         MVC   RCTDRCTR(4,R2),@CB00037                             0098 00039000
*                                                                  0099 00040000
*/********************************************************************/ 00041000
*/*                                                                  */ 00042000
*/*    THIS SECTION OF CODE WILL DO THE FOLLOWING PROCESSING TO      */ 00043000
*/*    RESCHEDULE PURGED I/O FOR ALL TASKS IN THE ADDRESS SPACE:     */ 00044000
*/*      - DETERMINE IF THERE WAS I/O PURGED AT QUIESCE TIME.        */ 00045000
*/*          - IF THERE WAS, DO THE FOLLOWING:                       */ 00046000
*/*             - SET UP REGISTER 1 POINTING TO THE                  */ 00047000
*/*               PURGE I/O REQUEST LIST (PIRL).                     */ 00048000
*/*             - SET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO INDICATE             */ 00049000
*/*               SVC 17 IS BEING INVOKED.                           */ 00050000
*/*             - ISSUE SVC 17 TO RESTORE I/O FOR                    */ 00051000
*/*               THIS ADDRESS SPACE.                                */ 00052000
*/*             - INDICATE NO I/O TO BE RESTORED. THIS               */ 00053000
*/*               IS NECESSARY TO INSURE SVC 17 IS NOT               */ 00054000
*/*               RE-INVOKED.                                        */ 00055000
*/*             - SET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO INDICATE I/O         */ 00056000
*/*               PROCESSING IS COMPLETE.                            */ 00057000
*/*                                                                  */ 00058000
*/********************************************************************/ 00059000
*                                                                  0099 00060000
*   IF RCTDBASEÂ¬=PRGNOIO THEN                                      0099 00061000
         CLC   RCTDBASE(3,R2),@CF00065+1                           0099 00062000
         BE    @RF00099                                            0099 00063000
*     DO;                                                          0100 00064000
*       R1=ADDR(RCTDPIRL);                                         0101 00065000
         LA    R1,RCTDPIRL(,R2)                                    0101 00066000
*       RCTDRS17='1'B;                                             0102 00067000
         OI    RCTDRS17(R2),B'10000000'                            0102 00068000
*       GEN( SVC 17);                                              0103 00069000
          SVC 17                                                        00070000
*       RCTDBASE=PRGNOIO;                                          0104 00071000
         MVC   RCTDBASE(3,R2),@CF00065+1                           0104 00072000
*       RCTDRIOC='1'B;                                             0105 00073000
         OI    RCTDRIOC(R2),B'10000000'                            0105 00074000
*     END;                                                         0106 00075000
*                                                                  0107 00076000
*/********************************************************************/ 00077000
*/*                                                                  */ 00078000
*/*    THIS SECTION OF CODE WILL DO THE FOLLOWING PROCESSING         */ 00079000
*/*    TO OBTAIN THE LOCAL LOCK AND ESTABLISH THE RECOVERY EXIT      */ 00080000
*/*    FOR THE LOCKED CODE:                                          */ 00081000
*/*      - SET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO INDICATE THE SETLOCK        */ 00082000
*/*        MACRO IS BEING INVOKED TO OBTAIN THE LOCAL LOCK.          */ 00083000
*/*      - ISSUE THE SETLOCK MACRO.                                  */ 00084000
*/*      - INVOKE THE SETCHECK SUBROUTINE TO CHECK THE RETURN        */ 00085000
*/*        CODE FROM SETLOCK.                                        */ 00086000
*/*      - SET UP A REGISTER WITH RESTORE'S FRR ADDRESS.             */ 00087000
*/*      - ISSUE THE SETFRR MACRO TO ESTABLISH THE RECOVERY          */ 00088000
*/*        ROUTINE FOR THE LOCKED CODE. THIS PLACES RESTORE'S        */ 00089000
*/*        FRR ADDRESS ON THE FRR LIFO STACK.                        */ 00090000
*/*    THE LOCK IS HELD PRIOR TO RESETTING RCT'S SUBTASKS            */ 00091000
*/*    DISPATCHABLE TO INSURE THAT NO TASKS WILL BE DISPATCHED       */ 00092000
*/*    UNTIL AFTER THE LONG WAIT PROCESSING CHECK.                   */ 00093000
*/*                                                                  */ 00094000
*/********************************************************************/ 00095000
*                                                                  0107 00096000
*   RCTDOBLK='1'B;                                                 0107 00097000
@RF00099 OI    RCTDOBLK(R2),B'01000000'                            0107 00098000
*OLOCLK:                                                           0108 00099000
*   GENERATE;                                                      0108 00100000
OLOCLK   DS    0H                                                  0108 00101000
     SETLOCK   OBTAIN,TYPE=LOCAL,MODE=UNCOND,                          X00102000
               RELATED=(TCB-PRIORITY-QUEUE,IEAVAR03(RLOCLK))            00103000
*   CALL SETCHECK;                                                 0109 00104000
         BAL   @14,SETCHECK                                        0109 00105000
*   RFY                                                            0110 00106000
*     R3 RSTD;                                                     0110 00107000
*   R3=ADDR(IEAVAFR3);                                             0111 00108000
         LA    R3,IEAVAFR3                                         0111 00109000
*   GEN( SETFRR A,FRRAD=(R3),WRKREGS=(FRRSPTR,FRREPTR));           0112 00110000
          SETFRR A,FRRAD=(R3),WRKREGS=(FRRSPTR,FRREPTR)                 00111000
*   RFY                                                            0113 00112000
*     R3 UNRSTD;                                                   0113 00113000
*                                                                  0114 00114000
*/********************************************************************/ 00115000
*/*                                                                  */ 00116000
*/*    THIS SECTION OF CODE WILL DO THE FOLLOWING PROCESSING         */ 00117000
*/*    TO RESET RCT'S SUBTASKS DISPATCHABLE:                         */ 00118000
*/*      - SET UP THE FOLLOWING REGISTERS FOR THE BRANCH ENTRY       */ 00119000
*/*        TO STATUS:                                                */ 00120000
*/*         - REGISTER 0                                             */ 00121000
*/*             BYTES 2-3    ENTRY CODE 10 INDICATING A              */ 00122000
*/*                          SECONDARY NON-DISPATCHABILITY           */ 00123000
*/*                          FLAG IS TO BE RESET IN ALL OF           */ 00124000
*/*                          RCT'S SUBTASKS.                         */ 00125000
*/*         - REGISTER 1                                             */ 00126000
*/*             BIT   0      1 - RESET IS BEING REQUESTED.           */ 00127000
*/*             BYTES 1-3    ADDRESS OF RCT'S TCB.                   */ 00128000
*/*         - REGISTER 13                                            */ 00129000
*/*             X'00001000'  INDICATES THE TCBNDTS BIT OF THE        */ 00130000
*/*                          TCBNDSP2 FLAG IS TO BE RESET.           */ 00131000
*/*      - SET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO INDICATE STATUS IS          */ 00132000
*/*        BEING INVOKED.                                            */ 00133000
*/*      - ISSUE A CALL TO THE STATUS ROUTINE USING ITS              */ 00134000
*/*        BRANCH ENTRY TO RESTART SUBTASKS.                         */ 00135000
*/*      - SET THE FOLLOWING RECOVERY FOOTPRINTS TO INDICATE:        */ 00136000
*/*         - STATUS PROCESSING COMPLETED.                           */ 00137000
*/*         - RCT'S SUBTASKS HAVE BEEN RESTARTED.                    */ 00138000
*/*                                                                  */ 00139000
*/********************************************************************/ 00140000
*                                                                  0114 00141000
*   RFY                                                            0114 00142000
*     R0 RSTD;                                                     0114 00143000
*   R0=TCBMASK;                                                    0115 00144000
         LA    R0,10                                               0115 00145000
*   R1=RESETMSK|R4;                                                0116 00146000
         LR    R1,R4                                               0116 00147000
         O     R1,@CF00060                                         0116 00148000

         L     R13,@CF00078                                        0117 00150000

*   CALL STATUSBR;                                                 0119 00153000

*                                                                  0123 00164000
*/********************************************************************/ 00165000
*/*                                                                  */ 00166000
*/*    IF RESTORE WAS ENTERED TO HANDLE QUIESCE BACKOUT, THE         */ 00167000
*/*    FOLLOWING PROCESSING WILL BE PERFORMED IN THIS SECTION:       */ 00168000
*/*      - INVOKE THE LOCKREL SUBROUTINE TO RELEASE THE              */ 00169000
*/*        LOCAL LOCK AND DELETE ITS RECOVERY EXIT.                  */ 00170000
*/*      - SET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO INDICATE SYSEVENT 18        */ 00171000
*/*        IS BEING INVOKED.                                         */ 00172000
*/*      - ISSUE THE SYSEVENT 18 MACRO TO INFORM THE SYSTEM          */ 00173000
*/*        RESOURCES MANAGER (SRM) OF QUIESCE BACKOUT.               */ 00174000
*/*      - SET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO INDICATE SRM                */ 00175000
*/*        PROCESSING COMPLETED.                                     */ 00176000
*/*      - RESET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT INDICATING                   */ 00177000
*/*        QUIESCE BACKOUT.                                          */ 00178000
*/*                                                                  */ 00179000
*/********************************************************************/ 00180000
*                                                                  0123 00181000
*   IF RCTDRSBO='1'B THEN                                          0123 00182000
         TM    RCTDRSBO(R2),B'10000000'                            0123 00183000

*     DO;                                                          0124 00185000
*       CALL LOCKREL;                                              0125 00186000

*/*                                                                  */ 00203000
*/*     IF RESTORE WAS ENTERED DUE TO AN ADDRESS SPACE BEING         */ 00204000
*/*     SWAPPED IN, THE FOLLOWING SECTIONS OF CODE WILL DO THE       */ 00205000
*/*     PROCESSING NECESSARY TO PREPARE THE ADDRESS SPACE FOR        */ 00206000
*/*     EXECUTION.                                                   */ 00207000
*/*                                                                  */ 00208000
*/********************************************************************/ 00209000
*/********************************************************************/ 00210000
*/*                                                                  */ 00211000
*/*      THIS SECTION OF CODE WILL DO THE FOLLOWING FOR LONG         */ 00212000
*/*      WAIT PROCESSING:                                            */ 00213000
*/*        - SET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO INDICATE LONG             */ 00214000
*/*          WAIT PROCESSING BEGINNING.                              */ 00215000
*/*        - CHECK THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO DETERMINE               */ 00216000
*/*          IF THE RESTORE SVC (SVC 17) WAS INVOKED TO              */ 00217000
*/*          RESTORE PURGED I/O. IF IT WAS, THEN THE                 */ 00218000
*/*          ADDRESS SPACE IS NOT IN LONG WAIT AND FURTHER           */ 00219000
*/*          TESTING IS UNNECESSARY.                                 */ 00220000
*/*        - TO CONTINUE LONG WAIT TESTING, CHECK FOR                */ 00221000
*/*          ANY ASYNCHRONOUS EXITS (IQES AND/OR RQES).              */ 00222000
*/*          IF ANY ARE QUEUED BUT NOT PROCESSED, THEN               */ 00223000
*/*          THE ADDRESS SPACE IS NOT IN LONG WAIT AND               */ 00224000
*/*          FURTHER TESTING IS UNNECESSARY.                         */ 00225000
*/*        - TO CONTINUE LONG WAIT TESTING, DETERMINE IF             */ 00226000
*/*          A TSB EXISTS. IF ONE EXISTS, ESTABLISH                  */ 00227000
*/*          ADDRESSABILITY TO IT AND CHECK FOR ANY                  */ 00228000
*/*          ATTENTION REQUESTS.  IF ANY EXIST, THEN THE             */ 00229000
*/*          ADDRESS SPACE IS NOT IN LONG WAIT AND FURTHER           */ 00230000
*/*          TESTING IS UNNECESSARY. ADDRESSABILITY TO THE           */ 00231000
*/*          TSB IS DELETED.                                         */ 00232000
*/*        - TO CONTINUE TESTING WHEN A TSB DOES NOT                 */ 00233000
*/*          EXIST OR THERE ARE NO ATTENTION REQUESTS,               */ 00234000
*/*          INVOKE THE TCBCHECK SUBROUTINE. THIS WILL               */ 00235000
*/*          SCAN THE TCB PRIORITY QUEUE LOOKING AT THE              */ 00236000
*/*          WAIT COUNT IN THE RBS AND THE NON-DISPATCHABILITY       */ 00237000
*/*          FLAGS IN EACH TCB IN SEARCH FOR A READY TASK.           */ 00238000
*/*          LONG WAIT TESTING IS COMPLETED HERE. IF THE             */ 00239000
*/*          READY STATUS WAS NOT FOUND, THEN THIS SUBROUTINE        */ 00240000
*/*          WILL SET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO INDICATE             */ 00241000
*/*          THE ADDRESS SPACE IS IN LONG WAIT.                      */ 00242000
*/*        - SET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO INDICATE LONG             */ 00243000
*/*          WAIT PROCESSING COMPLETE.                               */ 00244000
*/*        - INVOKE THE LOCKREL SUBROUTINE TO RELEASE                */ 00245000
*/*          THE LOCAL LOCK AND DELETE ITS RECOVERY EXIT.            */ 00246000
*/*                                                                  */ 00247000
*/********************************************************************/ 00248000
