*/*                                                                  */ 00300000
*/*      THIS SECTION OF CODE WILL DO THE FOLLOWING PROCESSING       */ 00301000
*/*      FOR TIMER WAIT LIMIT SUPPORT:                               */ 00302000
*/*        - SET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO INDICATE                  */ 00303000
*/*          WAIT LIMIT PROCESSING BEGINNING.                        */ 00304000
*/*        - IF THE ADDRESS SPACE IS NOT IN LONG WAIT AT RESTORE     */ 00305000
*/*          TIME AND THE CPU CLOCK IS NOT BAD, THEN CONTINUE        */ 00306000
*/*          TESTING TO PERFORM WAIT LIMIT SUPPORT.                  */ 00307000
*/*           - IF THE ADDRESS SPACE WAS NOT IN LONG WAIT WHEN       */ 00308000
*/*             SWAPPED OUT (AT QUIESCE TIME), THE FOLLOWING         */ 00309000
*/*             PROCESSING IS DONE SO THAT THE USER'S WAIT           */ 00310000
*/*             TIME LIMIT IS NOT CHARGED WITH THE SWAPPED           */ 00311000
*/*             OUT TIME:                                            */ 00312000
*/*               - ISSUE THE STORE CLOCK INSTRUCTION TO             */ 00313000
*/*                 GET THE CURRENT TIME.                            */ 00314000
*/*               - SUBTRACT THE TIME THE ADDRESS SPACE WAS          */ 00315000
*/*                 SWAPPED OUT FROM THE CURRENT TIME. THIS          */ 00316000
*/*                 AMOUNT IS THEN ADDED TO THE WAIT STATE           */ 00317000
*/*                 TIME STAMP FIELD.                                */ 00318000
*/*           - IF THE ADDRESS SPACE WAS IN LONG WAIT                */ 00319000
*/*             WHEN SWAPPED OUT (AT QUIESCE TIME), THE STORE        */ 00320000
*/*             CLOCK INSTRUCTION IS ISSUED TO STORE THE             */ 00321000
*/*             CURRENT TIME IN THE WAIT STATE TIME STAMP FIELD.     */ 00322000
*/*           IN EITHER CASE, THE WAIT STATE TIME STAMP FIELD        */ 00323000
*/*           IS UPDATED. TIMER SUPERVISION SUBTRACTS THIS           */ 00324000
*/*           FROM THE CURRENT TIME TO DETERMINE IF THE              */ 00325000
*/*           WAIT TIME LIMIT HAS ELAPSED FOR THIS ADDRESS           */ 00326000
*/*           SPACE.                                                 */ 00327000
*/*        - SET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO INDICATE WAIT             */ 00328000
*/*          LIMIT PROCESSING COMPLETED.                             */ 00329000
*/*                                                                  */ 00330000

*/*                                                                  */ 00494000
*/*    THIS SECTION OF CODE IS THE TCBCHECK SUBROUTINE WHICH         */ 00495000
*/*    WILL DO THE FOLLOWING PROCESSING TO DETERMINE IF THE          */ 00496000
*/*    ADDRESS SPACE IS IN LONG WAIT BY SCANNING THE TCB             */ 00497000
*/*    PRIORITY QUEUE FOR A READY TASK:                              */ 00498000
*/*      - ACCESS RCT'S FIRST SUBTASK.                               */ 00499000
*/*      - EXAMINE THE WAIT COUNT OF THE ASSOCIATED RB.              */ 00500000
*/*         - A ZERO WAIT COUNT MEANS THE RB IS READY TO RUN,        */ 00501000
*/*           SO EXAMINE THE TCB'S PRIMARY NON-DISPATCHABILITY       */ 00502000
*/*           FLAGS FOR A READY TASK. IF A READY TCB IS FOUND,       */ 00503000
*/*           THEN THE ADDRESS SPACE IS NOT IN LONG WAIT.            */ 00504000
*/*           IT IS UNNECESSARY TO CONTINUE TESTING SO THE           */ 00505000
*/*           FOLLOWING IS DONE:                                     */ 00506000
*/*             - RESTORE THE POINTER TO RCT'S TCB.                  */ 00507000
*/*             - RETURN CONTROL TO THE MAINLINE.                    */ 00508000
*/*         - FOR A NON-ZERO RB WAIT COUNT OR A NOT READY            */ 00509000
*/*           TCB, THEN IT IS NECESSARY TO CONTINUE SCANNING         */ 00510000
*/*           THE TCB PRIORITY QUEUE AND THE NEXT TCB IS             */ 00511000
*/*           ACCESSED. IF THE LAST TCB HAS BEEN EXAMINED            */ 00512000
*/*           WITHOUT A READY ONE BEING FOUND, THE FOLLOWING         */ 00513000
*/*           IS DONE:                                               */ 00514000
*/*             - SET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO INDICATE THE         */ 00515000
*/*               ADDRESS SPACE IS IN LONG WAIT.                     */ 00516000
*/*             - RESTORE THE POINTER TO RCT'S TCB.                  */ 00517000
*/*             - RETURN CONTROL TO THE MAINLINE.                    */ 00518000
*/*                                                                  */ 00519000
*/********************************************************************/ 00520000

*/*                                                                  */ 00563000
*/*    THIS SECTION OF CODE IS THE ABENDEXT SUBROUTINE. WHEN         */ 00564000
*/*    RESTORE RECEIVES AN UNEXPECTED RETURN CODE FROM A             */ 00565000
*/*    ROUTINE IT HAS INVOKED, THIS SUBROUTINE IS CALLED TO          */ 00566000

*/*    THIS SECTION OF CODE IS THE SETCHECK SUBROUTINE WHICH         */ 00588000
*/*    WILL DO THE FOLLOWING PROCESSING TO CHECK THE RETURN          */ 00589000

*/*           DETECTED ERROR.                                        */ 00598000
*/*                                                                  */ 00599000
*/********************************************************************/ 00600000

*   IF R13=0 THEN                                                  0203 00605000

*/*                                                                  */ 00621000
*/*           RESTORE'S FRR ROUTINE                                  */ 00622000
*/*                                                                  */ 00623000
*/*    THIS SECTION OF CODE WILL GET CONTROL IN THE EVENT            */ 00624000
*/*    OF ANY ERROR ENCOUNTERED DURING LOCKED CODE PROCESSING        */ 00625000
*/*    FROM RTM VIA A LOAD PSW. REGISTERS AT INPUT ARE AS            */ 00626000
*/*    FOLLOWS:                                                      */ 00627000
*/*        REGISTER  0       ADDRESS OF A 200 BYTE WORK AREA         */ 00628000
*/*        REGISTER  1       ADDRESS OF THE SDWA                     */ 00629000
*/*        REGISTERS 2 - 13  INVALID                                 */ 00630000
*/*        REGISTER  14      RETURN ADDRESS                          */ 00631000
*/*        REGISTER  15      ENTRY POINT ADDRESS                     */ 00632000
*/*                                                                  */ 00633000
*/********************************************************************/ 00634000
*/*                                                                  */ 00635000
*/*    THE FOLLOWING INITIAL PROCESSING IS PERFORMED TO:             */ 00636000
*/*      - ESTABLISH ADDRESSABILITY FOR THIS ROUTINE.                */ 00637000
*/*      - LOAD THE BASE REGISTER WITH THE ENTRY POINT               */ 00638000
*/*        ADDRESS.                                                  */ 00639000
*/*      - ESTABLISH ADDRESSABILITY TO THE SDWA.                     */ 00640000
*/*      - CHECK THE SDWA INDICATOR TO DETERMINE IF THE              */ 00641000
*/*        ERROR WAS IN THIS ADDRESS SPACE.                          */ 00642000
*/*          - NON-ZERO INDICATES NOT THIS ADDRESS SPACE,            */ 00643000
*/*            SO ISSUE THE SETRP MACRO SPECIFYING THE               */ 00644000
*/*            FOLLOWING WHEN RETURNING TO RTM:                      */ 00645000
*/*              - ADDRESS OF THE SDWA.                              */ 00646000
*/*              - CONTINUE WITH TERMINATION.                        */ 00647000
*/*          - ZERO INDICATES THIS ADDRESS SPACE, SO                 */ 00648000
*/*            CONTINUE FRR PROCESSING.                              */ 00649000
*/*                                                                  */ 00650000
*/********************************************************************/ 00651000
*                                                                  0209 00652000
*IEAVAFR3:                                                         0209 00653000
*   PROC OPTIONS(NOSAVE,NOSAVEAREA);                               0209 00654000
IEAVAFR3 DS    0H                                                  0210 00655000
*   RFY                                                            0210 00656000
*    (R9,                                                          0210 00657000
*     R6) RSTD;                                                    0210 00658000
*   GEN( USING  IEAVAFR3,R9);                                      0211 00659000
          USING  IEAVAFR3,R9                                            00660000
*   R9=R15;                                                        0212 00661000
         LR    R9,R15                                              0212 00662000
*   R6=R1;                                                         0213 00663000
         LR    R6,R1                                               0213 00664000
*   IF SDWAFMIDÂ¬=0 THEN                                            0214 00665000
         LH    @15,SDWAFMID(,R6)                                   0214 00666000
         N     @15,@CF02742                                        0214 00667000
         LTR   @15,@15                                             0214 00668000
         BZ    @RF00214                                            0214 00669000
*     DO;                           /* SETRP WKAREA(R6)RC(0)         */ 00670000
*       RESPECIFY                                                  0216 00671000
*        (GPR00P,                                                  0216 00672000
*         GPR01P,                                                  0216 00673000
*         GPR14P,                                                  0216 00674000
*         GPR15P) RSTD;                                            0216 00675000
*       GPR01P=R6;                                                 0217 00676000
         LR    GPR01P,R6                                           0217 00677000
*       GPR01P->SDWARCDE=0;         /* SAVE RC VALUE                 */ 00678000
         MVI   SDWARCDE(GPR01P),X'00'                              0218 00679000
*       RESPECIFY                                                  0219 00680000
*        (GPR00P,                                                  0219 00681000
*         GPR01P,                                                  0219 00682000
*         GPR14P,                                                  0219 00683000
*         GPR15P) UNRSTD;                                          0219 00684000
*     END;                                                         0220 00685000
*   ELSE                                                           0221 00686000
*     DO;                                                          0221 00687000
         B     @RC00214                                            0221 00688000
@RF00214 DS    0H                                                  0222 00689000
*                                                                  0222 00690000
*/********************************************************************/ 00691000
*/*                                                                  */ 00692000
*/*      THE ERROR WAS IN THIS ADDRESS SPACE.                        */ 00693000
*/*                                                                  */ 00694000
*/********************************************************************/ 00695000
*/*                                                                  */ 00696000
*/*      THIS SECTION OF CODE WILL DO THE FOLLOWING PROCESSING       */ 00697000
*/*      TO SET UP FOR RECORDING AND DIAGNOSING THE ERROR:           */ 00698000
*/*        - RE-ESTABLISH THE POINTER TO THE RCTD.                   */ 00699000
*/*        - CHECK THE LENGTH OF THE SDWA'S VARIABLE                 */ 00700000
*/*          RECORDING AREA TO INSURE THAT THE LENGTH                */ 00701000
*/*          OF THE INFORMATION TO BE RECORDED WILL NOT              */ 00702000
*/*          CAUSE OVERFLOW.                                         */ 00703000
*/*            - IF NO OVERFLOW WILL OCCUR, THEN THE                 */ 00704000
*/*              FOLLOWING PROCESSING IS DONE:                       */ 00705000
*/*                - CLEAR THE SDWA'S VARIABLE RECORDING             */ 00706000
*/*                  AREA.                                           */ 00707000
*/*                - GET THE LENGTH OF THE RECORDING AREA            */ 00708000
*/*                  USED.                                           */ 00709000
*/*                - RECORD RCT'S RECOVERY FOOTPRINTS.               */ 00710000
*/*                - RECORD ANY UNACCEPTABLE RETURN CODE             */ 00711000
*/*                  DETECTED IN RESTORE'S PROCESSING.               */ 00712000
*/*                - RECORD RCT'S CROSS COMMUNICATIONS FLAGS.        */ 00713000
*/*                - RECORD THE ASCB FLAGS FOR RCT.                  */ 00714000
*/*            - IF OVERFLOW WILL OCCUR, DO NOT                      */ 00715000
*/*              PERFORM ANY RECORDING.                              */ 00716000
*/*                                                                  */ 00717000
*/********************************************************************/ 00718000
*                                                                  0222 00719000
*       R2=PSAAOLD->ASCBASXB->ASXBRCTD;                            0222 00720000

*                                                                  0232 00742000
*/********************************************************************/ 00743000
*/*                                                                  */ 00744000
*/*      THIS SECTION OF CODE WILL DO THE FOLLOWING PROCESSING       */ 00745000
*/*      TO DIAGNOSE THE ERROR:                                      */ 00746000
*/*        - IF THE RESTART KEY WAS NOT THE CAUSE OF THE ERROR       */ 00747000
*/*          ERROR, THEN CONTINUE CHECKING.                          */ 00748000
*/*        - IF THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT INDICATES THAT STATUS         */ 00749000
*/*          PROCESSING WAS NOT COMPLETED, THEN CONTINUE             */ 00750000
*/*          CHECKING.                                               */ 00751000
*/*        - IF THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT INDICATES THAT STATUS         */ 00752000
*/*          WAS INVOKED, THEN CONTINUE CHECKING.                    */ 00753000
*/*        - IF THE ERROR WAS NOT DUE TO PERCOLATION OR              */ 00754000
*/*          THERE WAS AN ERROR IN THE PREVIOUS EXIT,                */ 00755000
*/*          THEN SET THE RECOVERY FOOTPRINT TO                      */ 00756000
*/*          INDICATE DUMP IS DESIRED.                               */ 00757000
*/*                                                                  */ 00758000
*/********************************************************************/ 00759000
*                                                                  0232 00760000
*       IF SDWARKEY='0'B THEN                                      0232 00761000
@RF00223 TM    SDWARKEY(R6),B'00100000'                            0232 00762000
         BNZ   @RF00232                                            0232 00763000

*/*      THIS SECTION OF CODE WILL DO THE FOLLOWING PROCESSING       */ 00781000

*/*          FOLLOWING WHEN RETURNING TO RTM:                        */ 00784000

./  ADD  SSI=71530109,NAME=IEAVAR04
         TITLE 'IEAVAR04 - ATTENTION EXIT SCHEDULER ROUTINE            *00001000
                        '                                               00002000
IEAVAR04 CSECT ,                                                   0001 00003000
@MAINENT DS    0H                                                  0001 00004000
         USING *,@15                                               0001 00005000
         B     @PROLOG                                             0001 00006000
         DC    AL1(16)                                             0001 00007000
         DC    C'IEAVAR04  76.030'                                 0001 00008000
         DROP  @15                                                      00009000
@PROLOG  STM   @14,@12,12(@13)                                     0001 00010000
         BALR  @08,0                                               0001 00011000
@PSTART  DS    0H                                                  0001 00012000
         USING @PSTART,@08                                         0001 00013000
RBPRFXLN EQU 64                                                         00014000
RBPRFLNA EQU 32                                                         00015000
PRBLEN   EQU 136                                                        00016000
SIRBLEN  EQU 200                                                        00017000
TIRBLEN  EQU 136                                                        00018000
IRBLEN   EQU 128                                                        00019000
SVRBLEN  EQU 200                                                        00020000
DECREG   DS    0H                                                  0051 00021000
*                                                                  0097 00022000
*/********************************************************************/ 00023000
*/*                                                                  */ 00024000
*/*  START  OF EXECUTABLE CODE                                       */ 00025000
*/*                                                                  */ 00026000
*/********************************************************************/ 00027000
*                                                                  0097 00028000
*   RCTDRCTR='08000000'X;           /* SET MODULE FLAG(RCTDATTN)   0097 00029000
*                                      WHILE RESETTING ALL OTHER   0097 00030000
*                                      FLAGS IN THE RCTDRCTR         */ 00031000
         L     @15,ASXBRCTD(,ASXBPTR)                              0097 00032000
         MVC   RCTDRCTR(4,@15),@CB02427                            0097 00033000
*/********************************************************************/ 00034000
*/*                                                                  */ 00035000
*/*  THE FOLLOWING SEGMENT WILL OBTAIN THE LOCAL LOCK                */ 00036000
*/*  UNCONDITIONALLY. IF A NON-ZERO RETURN CODE IS RETURNED          */ 00037000
*/*  AN ABEND WILL BE ISSUED. THE ABEND WILL BE PROCESSED            */ 00038000
*/*  BY RCT'S ESTAE ROUTINE.                                         */ 00039000
*/*                                                                  */ 00040000
*/********************************************************************/ 00041000
*                                                                  0098 00042000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0098 00043000
*     SETLK11 RESTRICTED;           /* REGISTERS 11,12,13            */ 00044000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0099 00045000
*     SETLK12 RESTRICTED;           /* AND 14 ARE USED BY            */ 00046000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0100 00047000
*     SETLK13 RESTRICTED;           /* THE SETLOCK MACRO.            */ 00048000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0101 00049000
*     SETLK14 RESTRICTED;           /* SETLOCK DOES NOT SAVE THE   0101 00050000

./  ADD  SSI=71530104,NAME=IEAVAR05
         TITLE 'IEAVAR05 - ATTENTION EXIT PROLOGUE ROUTINE             *00001000
                        '                                               00002000
IEAVAR05 CSECT ,                                                   0001 00003000
@MAINENT DS    0H                                                  0001 00004000
         USING *,@15                                               0001 00005000
         B     @PROLOG                                             0001 00006000
         DC    AL1(16)                                             0001 00007000
         DC    C'IEAVAR05  76.030'                                 0001 00008000
         DROP  @15                                                      00009000
@PROLOG  STM   @14,@12,12(@13)                                     0001 00010000
       USING IEAVAR05,15                                                00011000
       L 8,ENTRYPT                                                      00012000
       DROP 15                                                          00013000
       USING  IEAVAR05,8                                                00014000
RBPRFXLN EQU 64                                                         00015000
RBPRFLNA EQU 32                                                         00016000
PRBLEN   EQU 136                                                        00017000
SIRBLEN  EQU 200                                                        00018000
TIRBLEN  EQU 136                                                        00019000
IRBLEN   EQU 128                                                        00020000
SVRBLEN  EQU 200                                                        00021000
DECREG   DS    0H                                                  0046 00022000
*                                                                  0086 00023000
*/********************************************************************/ 00024000
*/*                                                                  */ 00025000
*/*   START OF EXECUTABLE CODE                                       */ 00026000
*/*                                                                  */ 00027000
*/********************************************************************/ 00028000
*                                                                  0086 00029000
*   TAXEPTR=IRBPTR;                 /* ESTABLISH BASE FOR TAXE       */ 00030000
         LR    TAXEPTR,IRBPTR                                      0086 00031000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0087 00032000
*     IRBPTR UNRESTRICTED;                                         0087 00033000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0088 00034000
*     SAVEPR13 RESTRICTED;                                         0088 00035000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0089 00036000
*     SAVEPR14 RESTRICTED;                                         0089 00037000
*   SAVEPR13=ENTREG13;              /* SAVE ADDR OF SAVE AREA        */ 00038000
         LR    SAVEPR13,ENTREG13                                   0090 00039000
*   SAVEPR14=ENTREG14;              /* SAVE RETURN ADDRESS           */ 00040000
         LR    SAVEPR14,ENTREG14                                   0091 00041000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0092 00042000
*     ENTREG13 UNRESTRICTED;                                       0092 00043000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0093 00044000
*     ENTREG14 UNRESTRICTED;                                       0093 00045000
*                                                                  0093 00046000
*/********************************************************************/ 00047000
*/*                                                                  */ 00048000
*/* IF THE TAXERESM FLAG IS ON THE TAXE HAS BEEN CANCELLED           */ 00049000
*/* BY ANOTHER ATTENTION REQUEST AND WILL RETURN TO SVC 3.           */ 00050000
*/*                                                                  */ 00051000
*/********************************************************************/ 00052000
*                                                                  0094 00053000
*   IF TAXERESM='0'B THEN           /* HAS EXIT BEEN CANCELLED       */ 00054000
         TM    TAXERESM(TAXEPTR),B'00010000'                       0094 00055000
         BNZ   @RF00094                                            0094 00056000
*     DO;                                                          0095 00057000
*       GENERATE CODE NOSETS NOFLOWS NODEFS NOREFS;                0096 00058000
           MODESET  KEY=NZERO,MODE=SUP                         @YM04244 00059000
*                                                                  0097 00060000
*/********************************************************************/ 00061000
*/*                                                                  */ 00062000
*/* CHECK IF TPUT HAS BEEN REQUESTED AND IF IT HAS, ISSUE            */ 00063000
*/* THE MESSAGE FOR THE ATTENTION EXIT                               */ 00064000
*/*                                                                  */ 00065000
*/********************************************************************/ 00066000
*                                                                  0097 00067000
*       IF STXOBUFÂ¬='00000000'X THEN/* TPUT REQUESTED?               */ 00068000
         L     @12,TAXEPARM(,TAXEPTR)                              0097 00069000
         L     @11,STXOBUF(,@12)                                   0097 00070000
         LTR   @11,@11                                             0097 00071000
         BZ    @RF00097                                            0097 00072000
*         DO;                                                      0098 00073000
*                                                                  0098 00074000
*/* SET UP THE INTERFACE FOR TPUT                                    */ 00075000
*                                                                  0099 00076000
*           RESPECIFY                                              0099 00077000
*             TPUTPR0 RESTRICTED;                                  0099 00078000
*           RESPECIFY                                              0100 00079000
*             TPUTPR1 RESTRICTED;                                  0100 00080000
*           RESPECIFY                                              0101 00081000
*             TPUTPR15 RESTRICTED;                                 0101 00082000
*           TPUTPR1=STXOBUF;        /* ADDRESS OF OUTPUT BUF         */ 00083000
         LR    TPUTPR1,@11                                         0102 00084000
*           TPUTPR0=STXOSIZ;        /* SIZE OF OUTPUT BUFFER         */ 00085000

*/*                                                                  */ 00474000
*/* THIS ROUTINE WILL RECEIVE CONTROL IN THE EVENT OF AN             */ 00475000

*/*                                                                  */ 00479000

*                                      AREA INTO THE SDWA AS POSSIBLE*/ 00519000
         BCTR  @12,0                                               0237 00520000
         EX    @12,@SM01766                                        0237 00521000
*           SDWAURAL=SDWAVRAL(2:2); /* MOVE LENGTH OF RECORD INTO  0238 00522000
*                                      SDWA                          */ 00523000
         MVC   SDWAURAL(1,SDWAPTR),SDWAVRAL+1(SDWAPTR)             0238 00524000
*         END;                                                     0239 00525000
*       ELSE                        /* NO                            */ 00526000
*         DO;                                                      0240 00527000
         B     @RC00235                                            0240 00528000
@RF00235 DS    0H                                                  0241 00529000
*           SDWAVRA(1:LENGTH(FRRWKA))=FRRWKA;/* MOVE FRR WORK AREA 0241 00530000
*                                      INTO RECORDING AREA           */ 00531000
         MVC   SDWAVRA(24,SDWAPTR),FRRWKA(FRRWKAP)                 0241 00532000
*           SDWAURAL=LENGTH(FRRWKA);/* MOVE LENGTH OF RECORD INTO  0242 00533000

         MVI   SDWAURAL(SDWAPTR),X'18'                             0242 00535000
*         END;                                                     0243 00536000
*       DO;                         /* SETRP RECORD(YES)WKAREA(SDWAPT   00537000

@RC00235 DS    0H                                                  0245 00540000
*         RESPECIFY                                                0245 00541000
*          (GPR00P,                                                0245 00542000
*           GPR01P,                                                0245 00543000
*           GPR14P,                                                0245 00544000
*           GPR15P) RSTD;                                          0245 00545000
*         GPR01P=SDWAPTR;                                          0246 00546000
*         GPR01P->SDWARCDE=4;       /* STORE RC INTO SDWA            */ 00547000
         MVI   SDWARCDE(GPR01P),X'04'                              0247 00548000
*         GPR01P->SDWARTYA=ADDR(IEAVART5);/* SAVE RETRY ADDRESS      */ 00549000
         LA    @12,IEAVART5                                        0248 00550000
         ST    @12,SDWARTYA(,GPR01P)                               0248 00551000
*         GPR01P->SDWARCRD='1'B;    /* TURN ON RECORD INDICATOR      */ 00552000
         OI    SDWARCRD(GPR01P),B'10000000'                        0249 00553000
*         GPR15P=ADDR(FRRMODID);    /* ACCESS RECORD PARAMETER LIST  */ 00554000
         LA    GPR15P,FRRMODID                                     0250 00555000
*         GPR01P->SDWARECP=GPR15P->I256C(1:24);/* COPY RECORD      0251 00556000
*                                      PARAMETERS                    */ 00557000
         MVC   SDWARECP(24,GPR01P),I256C(GPR15P)                   0251 00558000
*         RESPECIFY                                                0252 00559000
*          (GPR00P,                                                0252 00560000
*           GPR01P,                                                0252 00561000
*           GPR14P,                                                0252 00562000
*           GPR15P) UNRSTD;                                        0252 00563000
*       END;                                                       0253 00564000
*     END;                                                         0254 00565000
*   ELSE                            /* NO                            */ 00566000
*     DO;                                                          0255 00567000
         B     @RC00233                                            0255 00568000
@RF00233 DS    0H                                                  0256 00569000
*       DO;                         /* SETRP WKAREA(SDWAPTR)RC(0)    */ 00570000
*         RESPECIFY                                                0257 00571000

*     END;                                                         0262 00585000

@EF00002 DS    0H                                                  0266 00604000
@ER00002 BR    @14                                                 0266 00605000
*                                                                  0267 00606000
*/********************************************************************/ 00607000
*/*                                                                  */ 00608000
*/* THIS ROUTINE IS THE RETRY ROUTINE FOR THE ATTENTION EXIT         */ 00609000
*/* PROLOGUE ROUTINE. THIS ROUTINE WILL RECEIVE CONTROL AS A         */ 00610000
*/* RESULT OF THE FRR INDICATING RETRY. THIS ROUTINE WILL            */ 00611000
*/* DELETE THE FRR, RELEASE THE LOCAL LOCK AND WILL PRINT THE        */ 00612000
*/* ERROR MESSAGE. THIS ROUTINE WILL CALL SUBROUTINES THAT ARE       */ 00613000
*/* ALSO USED BY THE MAINLINE CODE.                                  */ 00614000
*/*                                                                  */ 00615000
*/********************************************************************/ 00616000
*                                                                  0267 00617000
*IEAVART5:                                                         0267 00618000
*   PROCEDURE OPTIONS(NOSAVE,NOSAVEAREA,NOPARMREG,RETREG);         0267 00619000
IEAVART5 DS    0H                                                  0268 00620000
*   GENERATE CODE NODEFS NOFLOWS NOSETS REFS(IEAVAR05,ENTRYPT);    0268 00621000
       USING *,15                                                       00622000
       L 8,ENTRYPT                                                      00623000
       DROP 15                                                          00624000
       USING IEAVAR05,8                                                 00625000
*   CALL FRRLOCK;                   /* RELEASE FRR AND LOCAL LOCK    */ 00626000
         BAL   @14,FRRLOCK                                         0269 00627000
*   CALL MSG;                       /* GO PRINT MESSAGE              */ 00628000
         BAL   @14,MSG                                             0270 00629000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0271 00630000
*     ENTREG14 RESTRICTED;                                         0271 00631000
*   ENTREG14=ADDR(CVTEXIT);         /* PLACE SVC 3 IN REG 14         */ 00632000
         L     ENTREG14,CVTPTR                                     0272 00633000
         LA    ENTREG14,CVTEXIT(,ENTREG14)                         0272 00634000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0273 00635000
*     ENTREG14 UNRESTRICTED;                                       0273 00636000
*RT5EXIT:                                                          0274 00637000
*   END IEAVART5;                   /* END OF RETRY                  */ 00638000

@EF00003 DS    0H                                                  0274 00640000
@ER00003 BR    @14                                                 0274 00641000
*                                                                  0275 00642000
*/********************************************************************/ 00643000
*/*                                                                  */ 00644000
*/* THIS ROUTINE WILL DELETE THE FRR AND WILL RELEASE THE            */ 00645000
*/* LOCAL LOCK. THE RETURN CODE FROM SETLOCK IS NOT CHECKED          */ 00646000
*/* TO SEE IF THE RELEASE WAS SUCCESSFUL.                            */ 00647000
*/*                                                                  */ 00648000
*/********************************************************************/ 00649000
*                                                                  0275 00650000

*   RESPECIFY                                                      0276 00654000
*     TEMPR14 RESTRICTED;                                          0276 00655000

*     FRRSPTR RESTRICTED;                                          0277 00657000

*   RESPECIFY                                                      0281 00665000

*   RESPECIFY                                                      0282 00667000

*                                                                  0295 00698000
*/********************************************************************/ 00699000
*/*                                                                  */ 00700000
*/* THIS PROCEDURE IS ENTERED WHEN THE MAINLINE CODE HAS             */ 00701000
*/* DETERMINED THAT AN UNEXPECTED SITUATION HAS OCCURRED             */ 00702000
*/* THAT WILL PREVENT THE USERS ATTENTION EXIT FROM                  */ 00703000
*/* RECEIVING CONTROL.  THIS ROUTINE IS GOING TO PRINT AN            */ 00704000
*/* ERROR MESSAGE THAT WILL NOTIFY THE TERMINAL USER THAT            */ 00705000
*/* THE ATTENTION EXIT IS GOING TO BE IGNORED.                       */ 00706000
*/*                                                                  */ 00707000

./  ADD  SSI=71330200,NAME=IEAVAR06
         TITLE 'IEAVAR06 - ATTENTION EXIT EPILOGUE ROUTINE             *00001000
                        '                                               00002000
IEAVAR06 CSECT ,                                                   0001 00003000
@MAINENT DS    0H                                                  0001 00004000
         USING *,@15                                               0001 00005000
         B     @PROLOG                                             0001 00006000
         DC    AL1(16)                                             0001 00007000
         DC    C'IEAVAR06  77.133'                                 0001 00008000
         DROP  @15                                                      00009000
@PROLOG  STM   @14,@12,12(@13)                                     0001 00010000
         BALR  @08,0                                               0001 00011000
@PSTART  DS    0H                                                  0001 00012000
         USING @PSTART,@08                                         0001 00013000
RBPRFXLN EQU 64                                                         00014000
RBPRFLNA EQU 32                                                         00015000
PRBLEN   EQU 136                                                        00016000

SVRBLEN  EQU 200                                                        00020000
DECREG   DS    0H                                                  0049 00021000
*                                                                  0087 00022000
*/********************************************************************/ 00023000
*/*                                                                  */ 00024000
*/*  START OF EXECUTABLE CODE                                        */ 00025000
*/*                                                                  */ 00026000
*/*  THE LOCAL LOCK IS HELD AT ENTRY FROM EXIT.                      */ 00027000
*/*                                                                  */ 00028000
*/*  THIS SEGMENT OF CODE WILL ESTABLISH A RECOVERY                  */ 00029000
*/*  ENVIRONMENT FOR THE LOCKED CODE OF THIS ROUTINE.                */ 00030000
*/*                                                                  */ 00031000
*/********************************************************************/ 00032000
*                                                                  0087 00033000
*   ENTREG13=RTNREG13;              /* SAVE ADDR OF SAVE AREA        */ 00034000
         LR    ENTREG13,RTNREG13                                   0087 00035000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0088 00036000
*     RTNREG13 UNRESTRICTED;                                       0088 00037000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0089 00038000
*     FRRSPTR RESTRICTED;                                          0089 00039000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0090 00040000
*     FRREPTR RESTRICTED;                                          0090 00041000
*   FRRSPTR=ADDR(IEAVAFR6);         /* ENTRY POINT TO FRR            */ 00042000
         LA    FRRSPTR,IEAVAFR6                                    0091 00043000
*   GENERATE CODE NODEFS NOSETS NOFLOWS REFS(FRRWKAP,FRRSPTR,FRREPTR,   00044000
*       PSACSTK,FRRSCURR,FRRSLAST,FRRSELEN,FRRSFRRA,FRRSPARM,PSALSFCC); 00045000

*   RESPECIFY                                                      0093 00048000
*     FRRSPTR UNRESTRICTED;                                        0093 00049000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0094 00050000
*     FRREPTR UNRESTRICTED;                                        0094 00051000
*                                                                  0095 00052000
*/********************************************************************/ 00053000
*/*                                                                  */ 00054000
*/* THE FOLLOWING SEGMENT OF CODE WILL RESET THE FLAGS IN            */ 00055000
*/* THE TAXE AND WILL SAVE THE ADDRESS OF THE TAXE IN THE            */ 00056000
*/* FRR WORK AREA.                                                   */ 00057000
*/*                                                                  */ 00058000
*/********************************************************************/ 00059000
*                                                                  0095 00060000
*   TAXEPTR=RBSECPTR;               /* ESTABLISH BASE REG FOR THE  0095 00061000
*                                      TAXE                          */ 00062000
         LR    TAXEPTR,RBSECPTR                                    0095 00063000
*   FRRTAXE=TAXEPTR;                /* SAVE THE TAXE POINTER         */ 00064000

*                                                                  0099 00069000
*/********************************************************************/ 00070000
*/*                                                                  */ 00071000
*/* THE FOLLOWING SEGMENT OF CODE WILL FREE THE TAIE IF              */ 00072000
*/* ONE WAS GOTTEN BY THE ATTENTION PROLOGUE ROUTINE                 */ 00073000
*/*                                                                  */ 00074000
*/********************************************************************/ 00075000
*                                                                  0099 00076000
*   IF TAXETAIEÂ¬='00000000'X THEN   /* IF THERE IS A TAIE FREE IT    */ 00077000
         L     @12,TAXETAIE(,TAXEPTR)                              0099 00078000
         LTR   @12,@12                                             0099 00079000
         BZ    @RF00099                                            0099 00080000
*     DO;                                                          0100 00081000
*       RESPECIFY                                                  0101 00082000

         OI    FRRGTFTI(FRRWKAP),B'10000000'                       0105 00091000

*                                                                  0108 00097000

*/* THE RETURN CODE FROM FREEMAIN WILL NOT BE CHECKED                */ 00099000
*/* BECAUSE THIS WAS A CONDITIONAL FREEMAIN                          */ 00100000

*       FRRCFFTI='1'B;              /* SET TRACKING FOOTPRINT        */ 00113000
         OI    FRRCFFTI(FRRWKAP),B'01000000'                       0114 00114000
*     END;                                                         0115 00115000
*                                                                  0116 00116000
*/********************************************************************/ 00117000
*/*                                                                  */ 00118000
*/* THE FOLLOWING SEGMENT OF CODE WILL CHECK TO SEE IF THE           */ 00119000
*/* TAXE IS TO BE FREED. IF IT IS THE TAXE WILL BE FREED             */ 00120000
*/* BY EXIT. THE TAXE MUST, HOWEVER BE DEQUEUED FROM THE             */ 00121000
*/* TAXE QUEUE                                                       */ 00122000
*/*                                                                  */ 00123000
*/********************************************************************/ 00124000
*                                                                  0116 00125000
*   IF RBFDYN='1'B THEN             /* IS TAXE TO BE FREED           */ 00126000

*     DO;                           /* YES                           */ 00129000
*       RESPECIFY                                                  0118 00130000
*         PTAXEPTR RESTRICTED;                                     0118 00131000
*       RESPECIFY                                                  0119 00132000
*         NTAXEPTR RESTRICTED;                                     0119 00133000
*       PTAXEPTR=PTAXEPTR-PTAXEPTR; /* CLEAR PREVIOUS PTR            */ 00134000
         SLR   PTAXEPTR,PTAXEPTR                                   0120 00135000

         L     @01,ASXBPTR(,ASCBPTR)                               0121 00137000
         L     @01,ASXBRCTD(,@01)                                  0121 00138000
         L     TAXEPTR,RCTDTAXE(,@01)                              0121 00139000

*         IF TAXEPTR=RBSECPTR THEN  /* CURRENT TAXE FOUND            */ 00143000

         BNE   @RF00123                                            0123 00145000
*           DO;                     /* YES                           */ 00146000
*             FRRTTBDQ='1'B;        /* SET A FOOTPRINT THAT A TAXE IS   00147000
*                                      TO BE DEQUEUED                */ 00148000
         OI    FRRTTBDQ(FRRWKAP),B'00100000'                       0125 00149000
*             IF PTAXEPTR='00000000'X THEN/* FIRST TAXE ON QUEUE     */ 00150000
         LTR   PTAXEPTR,PTAXEPTR                                   0126 00151000
         BNZ   @RF00126                                            0126 00152000
*               DO;                 /* YES                           */ 00153000
*                 RCTDTAXE=TAXELNK; /* DEQUEUE FIRST TAXE            */ 00154000
         L     @01,ASXBPTR(,ASCBPTR)                               0128 00155000

         ST    @00,RCTDTAXE(,@01)                                  0128 00159000
*               END;                                               0129 00160000
*             ELSE                  /* NO                            */ 00161000
*               DO;                                                0130 00162000
         B     @RC00126                                            0130 00163000

*                 NTAXEPTR=TAXELNK; /* SAVE NEXT TAXE PTR            */ 00165000

         LA    NTAXEPTR,0(,NTAXEPTR)                               0131 00167000
*                 TAXEPTR=PTAXEPTR; /* UPDATE BASE REG               */ 00168000

*                 FRRPTAXE=PTAXEPTR;/* SAVE PREVIOUS TAXE            */ 00170000
         ST    PTAXEPTR,FRRPTAXE(,FRRWKAP)                         0133 00171000

         STCM  NTAXEPTR,7,TAXELNK(TAXEPTR)                         0135 00175000
*               END;                                               0136 00176000
*             FRRTHBDQ='1'B;        /* SET FOOTPRINT FOR FRR         */ 00177000
@RC00126 OI    FRRTHBDQ(FRRWKAP),B'00010000'                       0137 00178000

         B     STATST                                              0138 00180000
*           END;                                                   0139 00181000

         LA    @15,0(,@15)                                         0141 00186000
         LR    TAXEPTR,@15                                         0141 00187000

         BNZ   @DL00122                                            0142 00190000

*       RESPECIFY                                                  0144 00193000
*         PTAXEPTR UNRESTRICTED;                                   0144 00194000
*     END;                                                         0145 00195000
*                                                                  0146 00196000
*/********************************************************************/ 00197000
*/*                                                                  */ 00198000
*/* THE SUBTASKS OF THE TCB THAT HAS THE EXITING TAXE ARE            */ 00199000
*/* RESTARTED USING THE BRANCH ENTRY TO STATUS START TCB             */ 00200000
*/*                                                                  */ 00201000
*/********************************************************************/ 00202000
*                                                                  0146 00203000
*STATST:                                                           0146 00204000
*   FRRGTSS='1'B;                   /* SET FOOTPRINT IND. THAT GOING    00205000
*                                      TO STATUS START               */ 00206000
@RF00116 DS    0H                                                  0146 00207000

*/* SET UP INTERFACE FOR STATUS START ALL SUBTASKS                   */ 00209000
*                                                                  0147 00210000

*     STATPR0 RESTRICTED;                                          0147 00212000

*   FRRCFSS='1'B;                   /* SET FOOTPRINT FOR FRR         */ 00230000

*                                                                  0160 00239000

*/*                                                                  */ 00241000
*/* THE FOLLOWING SEGMENT OF CODE WILL CHECK TO SEE IF               */ 00242000
*/* THERE ARE ANY TAXES ON THE QUEUE. IF THERE ARE THE               */ 00243000
*/* ENTIRE TAXE QUEUE WILL BE SEARCHED LOOKING FOR THE               */ 00244000
*/* HIGHEST LEVEL TAXE THAT HAS BEEN SCHEDULED.                      */ 00245000
*/*                                                                  */ 00246000
*/********************************************************************/ 00247000
*                                                                  0160 00248000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0160 00249000
*     PTAXEPTR RESTRICTED;                                         0160 00250000

*   RBSECPTR=ORIGTAXE;              /* RESTORE ORIG RB BASE          */ 00292000

*   RESPECIFY                                                      0178 00294000
*     ORIGTAXE UNRESTRICTED;                                       0178 00295000
*                                                                  0179 00296000
*/********************************************************************/ 00297000
*/*                                                                  */ 00298000
*/* THE TAXES FOLLOWING THE HIGHEST ACTIVE TAXE MUST BE              */ 00299000
*/* MARKED AVAILABLE FOR USE AND THEY MUST BE REFLECTED              */ 00300000
*/* IN THE TSBSTAX COUNT. THIS SEGMENT OF CODE WILL                  */ 00301000
*/* SEARCH THE ENTIRE TAXE QUEUE STARTING WITH THE HIGHEST           */ 00302000
*/* SCHEDULED TAXE AND PERFORM THE OPERATION.                        */ 00303000
*/*                                                                  */ 00304000
*/********************************************************************/ 00305000
*                                                                  0179 00306000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0179 00307000

*                                                                  0198 00359000
*/********************************************************************/ 00360000
*/*                                                                  */ 00361000
*/* UPDATE THE STAX COUNT IN THE TSB                                 */ 00362000
*/*                                                                  */ 00363000
*/* THE COUNT IS UPDATED USING COMPARE AND SWAP.                     */ 00364000
*/*                                                                  */ 00365000
*/* THE COUNT WILL NOT BE ALLOWED TO BE GREATER THAN 256             */ 00366000
*/* EVEN IF MORE TAXES EXIST.                                        */ 00367000
*/*                                                                  */ 00368000
*/********************************************************************/ 00369000
*                                                                  0198 00370000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0198 00371000

*/*                                                                  */ 00062000
*/* THE FOLLOWING SEGMENT OF CODE WILL ESTABLISH A RECOVERY          */ 00063000

*/*                                                                  */ 00065000
*/********************************************************************/ 00066000
*                                                                  0090 00067000
*       RESPECIFY                                                  0090 00068000
*         FRREPTR RESTRICTED;                                      0090 00069000
*       RESPECIFY                                                  0091 00070000

*       RESPECIFY                                                  0094 00079000
*         FRRSPTR UNRESTRICTED;                                    0094 00080000
*       RESPECIFY                                                  0095 00081000
*         FRREPTR UNRESTRICTED;                                    0095 00082000
*                                                                  0096 00083000
*/********************************************************************/ 00084000
*/*                                                                  */ 00085000
*/* THE FOLLOWING SEGMENT OF CODE WILL SEARCH THE TAXE               */ 00086000
*/* QUEUE LOOKING FOR TAXES THAT ARE FOR THE TERMINATING             */ 00087000
*/* TASK. IF A TAXE IS FOUND FOR THE TCB THE FOLLOWING               */ 00088000
*/* ACTIONS ARE TAKEN.                                               */ 00089000
*/*                                                                  */ 00090000
*/* IF THE TAXE IS AN ACTIVE RB THE RBFDYN FLAG WILL BE              */ 00091000
*/* SET SO THAT THE RB WILL BE FREED BY EXIT. ALL OTHER              */ 00092000
*/* PROCESSING THAT IS NECESSARY TO HOUSEKEEP THE TAXE               */ 00093000
*/* RESOURCE IS PERFORMED AT EXIT TIME BY IEAVAR06.                  */ 00094000
*/*                                                                  */ 00095000
*/* IF THE TAXE IS SCHEDULED BUT IS NOT AN ACTIVE RB                 */ 00096000
*/* THE TAXE IS DEQUEUED AND THE RBFDYN FLAG IS SET.                 */ 00097000
*/* THE TAXE IS DEQUEUED BECAUSE THE TAXE IS SCHEDULED               */ 00098000
*/* AS AN IQE THAT WILL BE DEQUEUED FROM THE IQE QUEUE               */ 00099000
*/* AND NEVER SCHEDULED. THE RBFDYN FLAG IS SET SO THAT              */ 00100000
*/* IF FOR ANY REASON THE TAXE(IQE) DOES BECOME AN ACTIVE            */ 00101000
*/* RB IT WILL BE FREED BY EXIT.                                     */ 00102000
*/*                                                                  */ 00103000
*/* IF THE TAXE IS DORMANT THE TAXE IS DEQUEUED AND THE              */ 00104000
*/* RBFDYN FLAG IS SET ONLY FOR CONVIENCE.                           */ 00105000
*/*                                                                  */ 00106000
*/* THE TAXES ARE NOT FREED BY THIS ROUTINE. THE TAXES               */ 00107000
*/* THAT ARE ACTIVE RB'S WILL BE FREED BY EXIT, THE IQES             */ 00108000
*/* AND DORMANT TAXES ARE FREED WHEN THE SUBPOOL STORAGE             */ 00109000
*/* FOR THIS TCB IS FREED. MOREOVER THE TAXES THAT ARE               */ 00110000
*/* ON THE IQE QUEUE CANNOT BE FREED BECAUSE THEY HAVE               */ 00111000
*/* NOT YET BEEN DEQUEUED FROM THE STAGE TWO EXIT                    */ 00112000
*/* EFFECTORS IQE QUEUE.                                             */ 00113000
*/*                                                                  */ 00114000
*/********************************************************************/ 00115000
*                                                                  0096 00116000
*       RESPECIFY                                                  0096 00117000

*         NTAXEPTR UNRESTRICTED;                                   0132 00203000
*                                                                  0133 00204000
*/********************************************************************/ 00205000
*/*                                                                  */ 00206000
*/* THE FOLLOWING SEGMENT OF CODE WILL CHECK TO SEE IF               */ 00207000
*/* THERE ARE ANY TAXES ON THE QUEUE. IF THERE ARE THE               */ 00208000
*/* ENTIRE TAXE QUEUE WILL BE SEARCHED LOOKING FOR THE               */ 00209000
*/* HIGHEST LEVEL TAXE THAT HAS BEEN SCHEDULED.                      */ 00210000
*/*                                                                  */ 00211000
*/********************************************************************/ 00212000
*                                                                  0133 00213000

*       DO WHILE TAXEPTRÂ¬='00000000'X;/* ANY MORE TAXES              */ 00220000

*         IF RBFACTV='1'B|TAXESCHD='1'B THEN/* IS THE TAXE ACT       */ 00223000

*       END;                                                       0141 00237000

         BNE   @DL00135                                            0141 00240000
*                                                                  0142 00241000
*/********************************************************************/ 00242000
*/*                                                                  */ 00243000
*/* THE TAXES FOLLOWING THE HIGHEST ACTIVE TAXE MUST BE              */ 00244000
*/* MARKED AVAILABLE FOR USE AND THEY MUST BE REFLECTED              */ 00245000
*/* IN THE TSBSTAX COUNT. THIS SEGMENT OF CODE WILL                  */ 00246000

*                                                                  0142 00251000

*                                                                  0162 00303000

*/*                                                                  */ 00305000
*/* UPDATE THE STAX COUNT IN THE TSB                                 */ 00306000
*/*                                                                  */ 00307000
*/* THE COUNT IS UPDATED USING COMPARE AND SWAP                      */ 00308000
*/*                                                                  */ 00309000
*/* THE COUNT WILL NOT BE ALLOWED TO BE GREATER THAN 255             */ 00310000
*/* EVEN IF MORE TAXES EXIST.                                        */ 00311000
*/*                                                                  */ 00312000

*/********************************************************************/ 00702000
*/*                                                                  */ 00703000
*/*                   ROUTINE TO SEARCH TAXE QUEUE                   */ 00704000
*/*                                                                  */ 00705000
*/*      THIS ROUTINE LOCATES THE FIRST TAXE QUEUED ON THE TAXE      */ 00706000
*/*      QUEUE FOR THE TCB THAT REQUESTED THIS SVC                   */ 00707000
*/*                                                                  */ 00708000
*/********************************************************************/ 00709000
*                                                                  0313 00710000
*SEARCH:                                                           0313 00711000
*   PROC OPTIONS(NOSAVE,NOSAVEAREA,NOPARMREG,NOENTREG,RETREG);     0313 00712000

*   TAXEPTR=RCTDTAXE;               /* POINT TO ADDRESS OF FIRST TAXE*/ 00714000

*   TAXEPREV=ZERO;                  /* STORE ZEROS IN PREVIOUS TAXE     00719000
*                                      POINTER                       */ 00720000

         ST    @10,TAXEPREV(,FRRWKAR)                              0315 00722000
*   IF RCTDTAXEÂ¬=ZERO THEN          /* CHECK IF NO TAXES QUEUED      */ 00723000

         BE    @RF00316                                            0316 00725000
*     DO WHILE TAXEPTRÂ¬=ZERO&TAXETCBÂ¬=TCBPTR;/* SEARCH TILL FIRST  0317 00726000
*                                      TAXE FOUND FOR THIS TCB       */ 00727000
         B     @DE00317                                            0317 00728000
@DL00317 DS    0H                                                  0318 00729000
*       TAXEPREV=TAXEPTR;           /* STORE ADDRESS OF THIS TAXE    */ 00730000
         ST    TAXEPTR,TAXEPREV(,FRRWKAR)                          0318 00731000
*       TAXEPTR=TAXELNK;            /* POINT TO NEXT TAXE IN QUEUE   */ 00732000
         SLR   @12,@12                                             0319 00733000

*   END SEARCH;                                                    0324 00751000

*/*                   INITIALIZE TAXES                               */ 00758000
*/*                                                                  */ 00759000
*/*        THIS ROUTINE INITILIALIZES THE TAXE WITH THE VALUES       */ 00760000
*/*        PASSED TO THIS SVC AT ENTRY                               */ 00761000

*/********************************************************************/ 00833000
*/*                                                                  */ 00834000
*/*                   QUEUING PROCESSING                             */ 00835000
*/*                                                                  */ 00836000
*/*         THIS ROUTINE QUEUES THE NEW TAXE TO ITS PROPER           */ 00837000
*/*         PLACE ON THE TAXE QUEUE. THE TAXE SHOULD BE PLACED       */ 00838000
*/*         ON THE QUEUE AS INDICATED BY THE FOLLOWING               */ 00839000
*/*         TWO RULES                                                */ 00840000
*/*           1. AN ATTENTION EXIT ROUTINE FOR A TASK WILL ALWAYS    */ 00841000
*/*              OCCUPY A HIGHER LEVEL THAN THE ATTENTION EXIT       */ 00842000
*/*              ROUTINE OF ANY OF ITS SUBTASKS                      */ 00843000
*/*           2. THE ATTENTION EXIT ROUTINE IS PLACED AT THE LOWEST  */ 00844000
*/*              POSSIBLE ATTENTION LEVEL, WITHOUT VIOLATING RULE 1  */ 00845000
*/*         THESE TWO RULES ARE DESIGNED TO ELIMINATE INTERLOCKS     */ 00846000
*/*         WHEN A SUBSTASK IS SET NON-DISPATCHABLE ACCROSS AN       */ 00847000
*/*         ATTENTION EXIT AND ANOTHER ATTENTION IS FIELDED          */ 00848000
*/*                                                                  */ 00849000
*/*                                                                  */ 00850000
*/********************************************************************/ 00851000
*                                                                  0348 00852000
*QUEUING:                                                          0348 00853000
*   PROC OPTIONS(NOSAVE,NOSAVEAREA,NOPARMREG,NOENTREG,RETREG);     0348 00854000
QUEUING  DS    0H                                                  0349 00855000
*   NEXTTAXE=RCTDTAXE;              /* INDICATE TAXE QUEUED AT HEAD     00856000
*                                      OF QUEUE                      */ 00857000

         L     @12,ASXBRCTD(,@12)                                  0349 00859000
         L     @12,RCTDTAXE(,@12)                                  0349 00860000
         ST    @12,NEXTTAXE(,FRRWKAR)                              0349 00861000
*   TAXEPREV=ZERO;                  /* INDICATE NO PREVIOUS TAXE     */ 00862000
         SLR   @10,@10                                             0350 00863000
         ST    @10,TAXEPREV(,FRRWKAR)                              0350 00864000
*   TAXEPTR=RCTDTAXE;                                              0351 00865000
         LR    TAXEPTR,@12                                         0351 00866000
*   IF TCBLTCÂ¬=ZERO THEN            /* CHECK IF THIS TCB HAS ANY SUB    00867000

*     DO;                                                          0390 00988000
*       TAXEPTR=NEWTAXE;            /* POINT TO NEW TAXE             */ 00989000

*       /*                                                           */ 00997000

*                                                                  0393 00999000
*       RFY                                                        0393 01000000

*/********************************************************************/ 01046000
*/*                                                                  */ 01047000
*/*                             FRR ROUTINE                          */ 01048000
*/*                                                                  */ 01049000
*/*         THIS ROUTINE WILL GET CONTROL IN THE EVENT OF ANY        */ 01050000
*/*         ERROR ENCOUNTERED DURING STAX SVC PROCESSING FROM        */ 01051000
*/*         RTM VIA A LOAD PSW. REGISTERS AT INPUT ARE AS FOLLOWS    */ 01052000
*/*             REGISTER 0 INVALID                                   */ 01053000
*/*             REGISTER 1 ADDRESS OF SDWA                           */ 01054000
*/*             REGISTERS 2 - 13 INVALID                             */ 01055000
*/*             REGISTER 14 RETURN ADDRESS                           */ 01056000
*/*             REGISTER 15 ENTRY POINT ADDRESS                      */ 01057000
*/*                                                                  */ 01058000
*/********************************************************************/ 01059000
*                                                                  0409 01060000
*STXFRR:                                                           0409 01061000
*   PROC OPTIONS(NOSAVE,NOSAVEAREA,NOPARMREG,NOENTREG,RETREG);     0409 01062000
STXFRR   DS    0H                                                  0410 01063000
*   GENERATE CODE NOSETS NODEFS NOFLOWS NOREFS;                    0410 01064000
           USING  STXFRR,6             ESTABLISH ADDRESSIBILITY         01065000
*                                      FOR THIS ROUTINE                 01066000
           LR     6,15                 LOAD BASE REGISTER WITH THE      01067000
*                                      ENTRY POINT ADDRESS              01068000
*   FRRWKAR=SDWAPARM;                                              0411 01069000
         L     FRRWKAR,SDWAPARM(,SDWAPTR)                          0411 01070000
*   IF SDWAFMID=ZERO THEN           /* CHECK IF ERROR IN THIS ADDRESS   01071000
*                                      SPACE                         */ 01072000
         ICM   @12,3,SDWAFMID(SDWAPTR)                             0412 01073000
         BNZ   @RF00412                                            0412 01074000
*     DO;                                                          0413 01075000
*       IF FRRDYSST=ON THEN         /* CHECK IF DEFER YES PROCESSING    01076000
*                                      STARTED                       */ 01077000
         TM    FRRDYSST(FRRWKAR),B'10000000'                       0414 01078000
         BNO   @RF00414                                            0414 01079000
*         DO;                                                      0415 01080000
*           RBSECPTR=FRRRBPTR;      /* POINT TO USERS RB             */ 01081000
         L     RBSECPTR,FRRRBPTR(,FRRWKAR)                         0416 01082000
*           RBATTN=OFF;             /* TURN DEFER BIT OFF            */ 01083000
         NI    RBATTN(RBSECPTR),B'11011111'                        0417 01084000
*         END;                                                     0418 01085000
*       IF FRRDNST=ON THEN          /* WAS DEFER NO PROCESSING     0419 01086000
*                                      STARTED                       */ 01087000
@RF00414 TM    FRRDNST(FRRWKAR),B'01000000'                        0419 01088000
         BNO   @RF00419                                            0419 01089000
*         DO;                                                      0420 01090000
*           RBSECPTR=FRRRBPTR;      /* POINT TO USERS RB             */ 01091000
         L     RBSECPTR,FRRRBPTR(,FRRWKAR)                         0421 01092000
*           RBATTN=ON;              /* TURN DEFER BIT ON             */ 01093000
         OI    RBATTN(RBSECPTR),B'00100000'                        0422 01094000
*         END;                                                     0423 01095000
*       IF FRRDYNST=ON THEN         /* CHECK IF TAXE WAS TO BE FREED    01096000
*                                      BY EXIT                       */ 01097000
@RF00419 TM    FRRDYNST(FRRWKAR),B'00100000'                       0424 01098000
         BNO   @RF00424                                            0424 01099000
*         DO;                                                      0425 01100000
*           RBSECPTR=FONDTAXE;      /* POINT TO RB IN TAXE           */ 01101000
         L     RBSECPTR,FONDTAXE(,FRRWKAR)                         0426 01102000
*           RBFDYN=OFF;             /* RESET FREE TAXE FLAG          */ 01103000
         NI    RBFDYN(RBSECPTR),B'11111101'                        0427 01104000
*         END;                                                     0428 01105000
